obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (5750)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5750&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Food Safety and`
  line `Standards Act, 2006.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint, and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act and`
  line `any reference in any such provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to`
  line `the coming into force of that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 15th October 2007 sections 4 to 10 (both inclusive), Sections 87, 88, 91 and 101 effective from 15th October 2007 vide Notification No.`
  line
  line `S.O.1758(E) see Gazette of India, extraordinary Part II, sec 3(ii).`
  line
  line `28th May, 2008 (ss. 3 and 30), vide notification No. S.O. 1246(E), dated 28th May, 2008, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `28th August, 2008 (s. 90), vide notification No. S.O. 2127(E), dated 28th August, 2008, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `18th November, 2008 (ss. 16, 17, 18, 81, 82, 83, 84, 85, 86, 92 and 93), vide notification No. S.O. 2678(E), dated 18th November, 2008, see`
  line `Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `9th March, 2009 (ss. 11, 12, 13, 14 and 15), vide notification No. S.O. 650(E), dated 9th March, 2009, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part`
  line `II, sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `31st July, 2009 Section 36 to 47 effective vide Notification No. S.O 1868(E) dated 31st July, 2009, see Gazette of India Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec 3(ii).`
  line
  line `29th June, 2009 Section 99 to be effective vide Notification No. S.O. 1575(E) dated 29th June, 2009, see Gazette of India Extraordinary, Part`
  line `II, sec 3(ii).`
  line
  line `29th July, 2010 Sections 19 to 21, Sections 23 to 29, Sections 31 to 35, Sections 48 to 80, Section 89, Section 94 to 98 and Section 100 to be`
  line `effective vide Notification No. S.O. 1855(E) dated 29th July, 2010, see Gazette of India Extraordinary, Part II, sec 3(ii).`
  line
  line `18th August, 2010 Section 22 [except in respect of matters relating to the genetically engineered or modified food as explained in clause (2) of`
  line `the Explanation] to be effective vide Notification No. S.O. 2038(E) dated 18th August, 2010, see Gazette of India Extraordinary, Part II, sec`
  line `3(ii).`
  line
  line `2nd November 2021, Clause (2) of Explanation of section 22, to be effective vide Notification No. S.O. 4601(E) dated 2nd November, 2021,`
  line `see Gazette of India Extraordinary, Part II, sec 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (5751)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Declaration as to expediency of control by the Union.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5751&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `It is hereby declared that it is expedient`
  line `in the public interest that the Union should take under its control the food industry.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (5752)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5752&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "adulterant" means any material which is or could be employed for making the food unsafe`
  line `or sub-standard or mis-branded or containing extraneous matter;`
  line
  line `(b) "advertisement" means any audio or visual publicity, representation or pronouncement made`
  line `by means of any light, sound, smoke, gas, print, electronic media, internet or website and includes`
  line `through any notice, circular, label, wrapper, invoice or other documents;`
  line
  line `(c) "Chairperson" means the Chairperson of the Food Authority;`
  line
  line `(d) "claim" means any representation which states, suggests, or implies that a food has particular`
  line `qualities relating to its origin, nutritional properties, nature, processing, composition or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(e) "Commissioner of Food Safety" means the Commissioner of Food Safety appointed under`
  line `section 30;`
  line
  line `(f) "consumer" means persons and families purchasing and receiving food in order to meet their`
  line `personal needs;`
  line
  line `(g) "contaminant" means any substance, whether or not added to food, but which is present in`
  line `such food as a result of the production (including operations carried out in crop husbandry, animal`
  line `husbandry or veterinary medicine), manufacture, processing, preparation, treatment, packing,`
  line `packaging, transport or holding of such food or as a result of environmental contamination and does`
  line `not include insect fragments, rodent hairs and other extraneous matter;`
  line
  line `(h) "Designated Officer" means the officer appointed under section 36;`
  line
  line `(i) "extraneous matter' means any matter contained in an article of food which may be carried`
  line `from the raw materials, packaging materials or process systems used for its manufacture or which is`
  line `added to it, but such matter does not render such article of food unsafe;`
  line
  line `(j) 'Food" means any substance, whether processed, partially processed or unprocessed, which is`
  line `intended for human consumption and includes primary food to the extent defined in clause (zk),`
  line `genetically modified or engineered food or food containing such ingredients, infant food, packaged`
  line `drinking water, alcoholic drink, chewing gum, and any substance, including water used into the food`
  line `during its manufacture, preparation or treatment but does not include any animal feed, live animals`
  line `unless they are prepared or processed for placing on the market for human consumption, plants, prior`
  line `to harvesting, drugs and medicinal products, cosmetics, narcotic or psychotropic substances:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may declare, by notification in the Official Gazette, any`
  line `other article as food for the purposes of this Act having regards to its use, nature, substance or`
  line quality;
  line
  line `(k) "food additive" means any substance not normally consumed as a food by itself or used as a`
  line `typical ingredient of the food, whether or not it has nutritive value, the intentional addition of which`
  line `to food for a technological (including organoleptic) purpose in the manufacture, processing,`
  line `preparation, treatment, packing, packaging, transport or holding of such food results, or may be`
  line `reasonably expected to result (directly or indirectly), in it or its by-products becoming a component`
  line `of or otherwise affecting the characteristics of such food but does not include contaminants or`
  line `substances added to food for maintaining or improving nutritional qualities;`
  line
  line `(l) "Food Analyst" means an analyst appointed under section 45;`
  line
  line `(m) "Food Authority" means the Food Safety and Standards Authority of India established under`
  line `section 4;`
  line
  line `(n) "food business" means any undertaking, whether for profit or not and whether public or`
  line `private, carrying out any of the activities related to any stage of manufacture, processing, packaging,`
  line `storage, transportation, distribution of food, import and includes food services, catering services, sale`
  line `of food or food ingredients;`
  line
  line `(o) "food business operator" in relation to food business means a person by whom the business is`
  line `carried on or owned and is responsible for ensuring the compliance of this Act, rules and regulations`
  line `made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(p) "food laboratory" means any food laboratory or institute established by the Central or a State`
  line `Government or any other agency and accredited by National Accreditation Board for Testing and`
  line `Calibration Laboratories or an equivalent accreditation agency and recognised by the Food Authority`
  line `under section 43;`
  line
  line `(q) "food safety" means assurance that food is acceptable for human consumption according to`
  line `its intended use;`
  line
  line `(r) "food safety audit" means a systematic and functionally independent examination of food`
  line `safety measures adopted by manufacturing units to determine whether such measures and related`
  line `results meet with objectives of food safety and the claims made in that behalf;`
  line
  line `(s) "Food Safety Management System" means the adoption Good Manufacturing Practices, Good`
  line `Hygienic Practices, Hazard Analysis and Critical Control Point and such other practices as may be`
  line `specified by regulation, for the food business;`
  line
  line `(t) "Food Safety Officer" means an officer appointed under section 37;`
  line
  line `(u) "hazard" means a biological, chemical or physical agent in, or condition of, food with the`
  line `potential to cause an adverse health effect;`
  line
  line `(v) "import" means bringing into India any article of food by land, sea or air;`
  line
  line `(w) "improvement notice" means a notice issued under section 32 of this Act;`
  line
  line `(x) "infant food" and "infant milk" substitute shall have the meanings assigned to them in clauses`
  line `(f) and (g) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Infant Milk Substitutes, Feeding Bottles and Infant`
  line `Foods (Regulation of Production, Supply and Distribution) Act, 1992 (41 of 1992), respectively;`
  line
  line `(y) "ingredient" means any substance, including a food additive used in the manufacture or`
  line `preparation of food and present in the final product, possibly in a modified form;`
  line
  line `(z) 'label" means any tag, brand, mark, pictorial or other descriptive matter, written, printed,`
  line `stencilled, marked, embossed, graphic, perforated, stamped or impressed on or attached to container,`
  line `cover, lid or crown of any food package and includes a product insert;`
  line
  line `(za) "licence" means a licence granted under section 31;`
  line
  line `(zb) 'local area' means any area, whether urban or rural, notified by the Commissioner of Food`
  line `Safety, to be a local area for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(zc) "manufacture" means a process or adoption or any treatment for conversion of ingredients`
  line `into an article of food, which includes any sub-process, incidental or ancillary to the manufacture of`
  line `an article of food;`
  line
  line `(zd) "manufacturer" means a person engaged in the business of manufacturing any article of food`
  line `for sale and includes any person who obtains such article from another person and packs and labels it`
  line `for sale or only labels it for such purposes;`
  line
  line `^1[(ze) "Member" includes a part-time Member and the Chairperson of the Food Authority;]`
  line
  line `(zf) "misbranded food" means an article of food--`
  line
  line `(A) if it is purported, or is represented to be, or is being--`
  line
  line `(i) offered or promoted for sale with false, misleading or deceptive claims either;`
  line
  line `(a) upon the label of the package, or`
  line
  line `(b) through advertisement, or`
  line
  line `(ii) sold by a name which belongs to another article of food; or`
  line
  line `(iii) offered or promoted for sale under the name of a fictitious individual or company as`
  line `the manufacturer or producer of the article as borne on the package or containing the article`
  line `or the label on such package; or`
  line
  line `(B) if the article is sold in packages which have been sealed or prepared by or at the instance`
  line `of the manufacturer or producer bearing his name and address but--`
  line
  line `(i) the article is an imitation of, or is a substitute for, or resembles in a manner likely to`
  line `deceive, another article of food under the name of which it is sold, and is not plainly and`
  line `conspicuously labelled so as to indicate its true character; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the package containing the article or the label on the package bears any statement,`
  line `design or device regarding the ingredients or the substances contained therein, which is false`
  line `or misleading in any material particular, or if the package is otherwise deceptive with respect`
  line `to its contents; or`
  line
  line `(iii) the article is offered for sale as the product of any place or country which is false; or`
  line
  line `(C) if the article contained in the package--`
  line
  line `(i) contains any artificial flavouring, colouring or chemical preservative and the package`
  line `is without a declaratory label stating that fact or is not labelled in accordance with the`
  line `requirements of this Act or regulations made thereunder or is in contravention thereof; or`
  line
  line `(ii) is offered for sale for special dietary uses, unless its label bears such information as`
  line `may be specified by regulation, concerning its vitamins, minerals or other dietary properties`
  line `in order sufficiently to inform its purchaser as to its value for such use; or`
  line
  line `(iii) is not conspicuously or correctly stated on the outside thereof within the limits of`
  line `variability laid down under this Act.`
  line
  line `(zg) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(zh) "package" means a pre-packed box, bottle, casket, tin, barrel, case, pouch, receptacle, sack,`
  line `bag, wrapper or such other things in which an article of food is packed;`
  line
  line `(zi) "premises" include any shop, stall, hotel, restaurant, airline services and food canteens, place`
  line `or vehicle or vessel where any article of food is sold or manufactured or stored for sale;`
  line
  line `(zj) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made by the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government, as the case may be under this Act;`
  line
  line `(zk) "primary food" means an article of food, being a produce of agriculture or horticulture or`
  line `animal husbandry and dairying or aquaculture in its natural form, resulting from the growing, raising,`
  line `cultivation, picking, harvesting, collection or catching in the hands of a person other than a farmer or`
  line fisherman;
  line
  line `(zl) "prohibition order" means an order issued under section 33 of this Act;`
  line
  line `(zm) "risk", in relation to any article of food, means the probability of an adverse effect on the`
  line `health of consumers of such food and the severity of that effect, consequential to a food hazard;`
  line
  line `(zn) "risk analysis", in relation to any article of food, means a process consisting of three`
  line `components, i.e. risk assessment, risk management and risk communication;`
  line
  line `(zo) "risk assessment" means a scientifically based process consisting of the following steps:`
  line `(i) hazard identification, (ii) hazard characterisation; (iii) exposure assessment, and (iv) risk`
  line haracterisation;
  line
  line `(zp) "risk communication" means the interactive exchange of information and opinions`
  line `throughout the risk analysis process concerning risks, risk-related factors and risk perceptions,`
  line `among risk assessors, risk managers, consumers, industry, the academic community and other`
  line `interested parties, including the explanation of risk assessment findings and the basis of risk`
  line `management decisions;`
  line
  line `(zq) "risk management" means the process, distinct from risk assessment, of evaluating policy`
  line `alternatives, in consultation with all interested parties considering risk assessment and other factors`
  line `relevant for the protection of health of consumers and for the promotion of fair trade practices, and, if`
  line `needed, selecting appropriate prevention and control options;`
  line
  line `(zr)"sale" with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, means the sale of any article`
  line `of food, whether for cash or on credit or by way of exchange and whether by wholesale or retail, for`
  line `human consumption or use, or for analysis, and includes an agreement for sale, an offer for sale, the`
  line `exposing for sale or having in possession for sale of any such article, and includes also an attempt to`
  line `sell any such article;`
  line
  line `(zs) "sample" means a sample of any article of food taken under the provisions of this Act or any`
  line `rules and regulations made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(zt) 'specified by regulations" means specified by regulations made by the Food Authority;`
  line
  line `(zu) "standard", in relation to any article of food, means the standards notified by the Food`
  line Authority;
  line
  line `(zv)"State Government" in relation to a Union territory" means the Administrator of that Union`
  line `territory appointed by the President under article 239 of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(zw) "substance" includes any natural or artificial substance or other matter, whether it is in a`
  line `solid state or in liquid form or in the form of gas or vapour;`
  line
  line `(zx) "sub-standard" an article of food shall be deemed to be sub-standard if it does not meet the`
  line `specified standards but not so as to render the article of food unsafe;`
  line
  line `(zy) 'Tribunal" means the Food Safety Appellate Tribunal established under section 70;`
  line
  line `(zz) "unsafe food" means an article of food whose nature, substance or quality is so affected as to`
  line `render it injurious to health:--`
  line
  line `(i) by the article itself, or its package thereof, which is composed, whether wholly or in`
  line `part, of poisonous or deleterious substances; or`
  line
  line `(ii) by the article consisting, wholly or in part, of any filthy, putrid, rotten, decomposed`
  line `or diseased animal substance or vegetable substance; or`
  line
  line `(iii) by virtue of its unhygienic processing or the presence in that article of any harmful`
  line `substance; or`
  line
  line `(iv) by the substitution of any inferior or cheaper substance whether wholly or in part; or`
  line
  line `(v) by addition of a substance directly or as an ingredient which is not permitted; or`
  line
  line `(vi) by the abstraction, wholly or in part, of any of its constituents; or`
  line
  line `(vii) by the article being so coloured, flavoured or coated, powdered or polished, as to`
  line `damage or conceal the article or to make it appear better or of greater value than it really is;`
  line or
  line
  line `(viii) by the presence of any colouring matter or preservatives other than that specified in`
  line `respect thereof; or`
  line
  line `(ix) by the article having been infected or infested with worms, weevils, or insects; or`
  line
  line `(x) by virtue of its being prepared, packed or kept under insanitary conditions; or`
  line
  line `(xi) by virtue of its being mis-branded or sub-standard or food containing extraneous`
  line `matter; or`
  line
  line `(xii) by virtue of containing pesticides and other contaminants in excess of quantities`
  line `specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) Any reference in this Act to a law which is not in force in the State of Jammu and Kashmir* shall,`
  line `in relation to that State, be construed as a reference to the corresponding Law, if any, in force in that`
  line State.
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs.by Act 13 of 2008, s. 2, for cl. (ze) (w.e.f. 7-2-2008).`
  line
  line `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (5753)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Establishment of Food Safety and Standards Authority of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5753&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government`
  line `shall, by notification, establish a body to be known as the Food Safety and Standards Authority of India`
  line `to exercise the powers conferred on, and to perform the functions assigned to, it under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Food Authority shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having perpetual succession`
  line `and a common seal with power to acquire, hold and dispose of property, both movable and immovable,`
  line `and to contract and shall, by the said name, sue or be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The head office of the Food Authority shall be at Delhi.`
  line
  line `(4) The Food Authority may establish its offices at any other place in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (5754)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Composition of Food Authority and qualifications for appointment of its Chairperson and other Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 13 of 2008, s. 3, for sub-sections (4) and (5) (w.e.f. 7-2-2008)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5754&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Food Authority shall consist of a Chairperson and the following twenty-two`
  line `members out of which one-third shall be women, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) seven Members, not below the rank of a Joint Secretary to the Government of India, to be`
  line `appointed by the Central Government, to respectively represent the Ministries or Departments of the`
  line `Central Government dealing with--`
  line
  line `(i) Agriculture,`
  line
  line `(ii) Commerce,`
  line
  line `(iii) Consumer Affairs,`
  line
  line `(iv) Food Processing,`
  line
  line `(v) Health,`
  line
  line `(vi) Legislative Affairs,`
  line
  line `(vii) Small Scale Industries,`
  line
  line `(viii) who shall be Members ex officio;`
  line
  line `(b) two representatives from food industry of which one shall be from small scale industries;`
  line
  line `(c) two representatives from consumer organisations;`
  line
  line `(d) three eminent food technologists or scientists;`
  line
  line `(e) five members to be appointed by rotation every three years, one each in seriatim from the`
  line `Zones as specified in the First Schedule to represent the States and the Union territories;`
  line
  line `(f) two persons to represent farmers' organisations;`
  line
  line `(g) one person to represent retailers' organisations.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson and other Members of the Food Authority shall be appointed in such a manner`
  line `so as to secure the highest standards of competence, broad range of relevant expertise, and shall`
  line `represent, the broadest possible geographic distribution within the country.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson shall be appointed by the Central Government from amongst the persons of`
  line `eminence in the field of food science or from amongst the persons from the administration who have`
  line `been associated with the subject and is either holding or has held the position of not below the rank of`
  line `Secretary to the Government of India.`
  line
  line `^1[(4) The Chairperson and the Members including part-time Members other than the ex officio`
  line `embers of the Food Authority may be appointed by the Central Government on the recommendations of`
  line `the Selection Committee.`
  line
  line `(5) The Chairperson of the Food Authority shall not hold any other office.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (5755)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Selection Committee for selection of Chairperson and Members of Food Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5755&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Central Government shall, for the purpose of selection of the Chairperson and the Members other than ex officio Members of the Food Authority, constitute a Selection Committee consisting of--`
  line
  line `(a) Cabinet Secretary-Chairperson,`
  line
  line `(b) Secretary-in-charge of the Ministry or the Department responsible for administration of this`
  line `Act as the convenerMember,`
  line
  line `(c) Secretary-in-charge of the Ministries or the Departments of the Central Government dealing`
  line `with Health, Legislative and Personnel Members,`
  line
  line `(d) Chairman of the Public Enterprises Selection Board Member,`
  line
  line `(e) An eminent food technologist to be nominated by the Central GovernmentMember.`
  line
  line `Explanation - For the purposes of clause (e), the Central Government shall nominate a person`
  line `from amongst persons holding the post of Director or the Head, by whatever name called, of any`
  line `national research or technical institution.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall, within two months from the date of occurrence of any vacancy by`
  line `reason of death, resignation, or removal of the Chairperson or a Member of the Food Authority and three`
  line `months before the superannuation or completion of the term of office of the Chairperson or any Member`
  line `of that Authority, make a reference to the Selection Committee for filling up of the vacancy.`
  line
  line `(3) The Selection Committee shall finalise the selection of the Chairperson and Members of the Food`
  line `Authority within two months from the date on which the reference is made to it.`
  line
  line `(4) The Selection Committee shall recommend a panel of two names for every vacancy referred to it.`
  line
  line `(5) Before recommending any person for appointment as a Chairperson or other Member of the Food`
  line `Authority, the Selection Committee shall satisfy itself that such person does not have any financial or`
  line `other interest, which is likely to affect prejudicially his functions as a Member.`
  line
  line `(6) No appointment of the Chairperson or other Member of the Food Authority shall be invalid`
  line `merely by reason of any vacancy in the Selection Committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (5756)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Term of office, salary, allowances and other conditions of service of Chairperson and Members of Food Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1 . Subs.by Act 13 of 2008, s. 4, for the proviso (w.e.f. 7-2-2008).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5756&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson and the members other than ex officio Members`
  line `shall hold office for a term of three years from the date on which they enter upon their offices, and shall`
  line `be eligible for re-appointment for a further period of three years:`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[Provided that the Chairperson shall not hold office as such after he has attained the age of sixty-five`
  line years.]
  line
  line `(2) The salary and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `Chairperson and Members other than ex officio Members shall be such as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson and every Member shall, before entering upon his office, make and subscribe to`
  line `an oath of office and of secrecy in such form and in such manner and before such authority as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section the Chairperson or any Member may`
  line
  line `(a) relinquish his office by giving in writing to the Central Government a notice of not less than`
  line `three months; or`
  line
  line `(b) be removed from his office in accordance with the provisions of section 8.`
  line
  line `(5) The Chairperson or any Member ceasing to hold office as such shall not represent any person`
  line `before the Food Authority or any State Authority in any manner.`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (5757)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Removal of Chairperson and Members of Food Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5757&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in sub-section (1) of section 7, the Central Government may, by order, remove from office the`
  line `Chairperson or any other Member, if the Chairperson or as the case may be, such other Member,--`
  line
  line `(a) has been adjudged an insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the Central Government, involves`
  line `moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(c) has become physically or mentally incapable of acting as a Member; or`
  line
  line `(d) has acquired such financial or other interests as is likely to affect prejudicially his functions`
  line `as a Member; or`
  line
  line `(e) has so abused his position as to render his continuance in office prejudicial to the public`
  line interest.
  line
  line `(2) No Member shall be removed under clauses (d) and (e) of sub-section (1) unless he has been`
  line `given a reasonable opportunity of being heard in the matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (5758)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Officers and other employees of Food Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5758&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a Chief Executive Officer`
  line `of the Food Authority, not below the rank of Additional Secretary to the Government of India, who shall`
  line `be the Member-Secretary of the Authority, to be appointed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Food Authority may, with the approval of the Central Government, determine the number,`
  line `nature and categories of other officers and employees required to the Food Authority in the discharge of`
  line `its functions.`
  line
  line `(3) The salaries and allowances payable to and other conditions of service of, the Chief Executive`
  line `Officer, officers, and other employees shall be such as may be specified by regulations by the Food`
  line `Authority with the approval of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (5759)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Functions of the Chief Executive Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5759&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Executive Officer shall be the legal`
  line `representative of the Food Authority and shall be responsible for--`
  line
  line `(a) the day-to-day administration of the Food Authority;`
  line
  line `(b) drawing up of proposal for the Food Authoritys work programmes in consultation with the`
  line `Central Advisory Committee;`
  line
  line `(c) implementing the work programmes and the decisions adopted by the Food Authority;`
  line
  line `(d) ensuring the provision of appropriate scientific, technical and administrative support for the`
  line `Scientific Committee and the Scientific Panel;`
  line
  line `(e) ensuring that the Food Authority carries out its tasks in accordance with the requirements of`
  line `its users, in particular with regard to the adequacy of the services provided and the time taken;`
  line
  line `(f) the preparation of the statement of revenue and expenditure and the execution of the budget of`
  line `the Food Authority; and`
  line
  line `(g) developing and maintaining contact with the Central Government, and for ensuring a regular`
  line `dialogue with its relevant committees.`
  line
  line `(2) Every year, the Chief Executive Officer shall submit to the Food Authority for approval`
  line
  line `(a) a general report covering all the activities of the Food Authority in the previous year;`
  line
  line `(b) programmes of work;`
  line
  line `(c) the annual accounts for the previous year; and`
  line
  line `(d) the budget for the coming year.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chief Executive Officer shall, following adoption by the Food Authority, forward, the`
  line `general report and the programmes to the Central Government and the State Governments and shall have`
  line `them published.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chief Executive Officer shall approve all financial expenditure of the Food Authority and`
  line `report on the Authoritys activities to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) The Chief Executive Officer shall exercise the powers of the Commissioner of Food Safety while`
  line `dealing with matters relating to food safety of such articles.`
  line
  line `(6) The Chief Executive Officer shall have administrative control over the officers and other`
  line `employees of the Food Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (5760)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Central Advisory Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5760&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Food Authority shall, by notification, establish a`
  line `Committee to be known as the Central Advisory Committee.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Advisory Committee shall consist of two members each to represent the interests of`
  line `food industry, agriculture, consumers, relevant research bodies and food laboratories and all`
  line `Commissioners of Food Safety, and the Chairperson of the Scientific Committee shall be ex officio`
  line member.
  line
  line `(3) The representatives of the concerned Ministries or Departments of the Central Government in`
  line `Agriculture, Animal Husbandry and Dairying, Bio-technology, Commerce and Industry, Consumer`
  line `Affairs, Environment and Forests, Food Processing Industries, Health, Panchayati Raj, Small Scale`
  line `Industries and Food and Public Distribution or government institutes or organisations and government`
  line `recognised farmers shall be invitees to the deliberations of the Central Advisory Committee.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chief Executive Officer shall be ex officio Chairperson of the Central Advisory Committee.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Advisory Committee shall follow such rules of procedure including its transaction of`
  line `business as may be specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (5761)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Functions of Central Advisory Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5761&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Advisory Committee shall ensure`
  line `close cooperation between the Food Authority and the enforcement agencies and organisations operating`
  line `in the field of food.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Advisory Committee shall advise the Food Authority on`
  line
  line `(a) the performance of its duties under this section and in particular in drawing up of a proposal`
  line `for the Food Authoritys work programme,`
  line
  line `(b) on the prioritisation of work,`
  line
  line `(c) identifying potential risks,`
  line
  line `(d) pooling of knowledge, and`
  line
  line `(e) such other functions as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Advisory Committee shall meet regularly at the invitation of the Chairperson of`
  line `Central Advisory Committee or at the request of at least one-third of its members, and not less than three`
  line `times a year.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (5762)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Scientific Panels.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5762&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Food Authority shall establish scientific panels, which shall consist of`
  line `independent scientific experts.`
  line
  line `(2) The Scientific Panel shall invite the relevant industry and consumer representatives in its`
  line deliberations.
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Food Authority may establish as many`
  line `Scientific Panels as it considers necessary in addition to the Panels on:`
  line
  line `(a) food additives, flavourings, processing aids and materials in contact with food;`
  line
  line `(b) pesticides and antibiotics residues;`
  line
  line `(c) genetically modified organisms and foods;`
  line
  line `(d) functional foods, nutraceuticals, dietetic products and other similar products;`
  line
  line `(e) biological hazards;`
  line
  line `(f) contaminants in the food chain;`
  line
  line `(g) labelling; and`
  line
  line `(h) method of sampling and analysis.`
  line
  line `(4) The Food Authority may from time to time re-constitute the Scientific Panels by adding new`
  line `members or by omitting the existing members or by changing the name of the panel as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (5763)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Scientific Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5763&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Food Authority shall constitute Scientific Committee which shall`
  line `consist of the Chairpersons of the Scientific Panels and six independent scientific experts not belonging or`
  line
  line `affiliated to any of the Scientific Panels.`
  line
  line `(2) The Scientific Committee shall be responsible for providing the scientific opinions to the Food`
  line `Authority, and shall have the powers, where necessary, of organising public hearings.`
  line
  line `(3) The Scientific Committee shall be responsible for the general co-ordination necessary to ensure`
  line `consistency of the scientific opinion procedure and in particular with regard to the adoption of working`
  line `procedures and harmonisation of working methods of the Scientific Panels.`
  line
  line `(4) The Scientific Committee shall provide opinions on multi-sectoral issues falling within the`
  line `competence of more than one Scientific Panel, and on issues which do not fall within the competence of`
  line `any of the Scientific Panels.`
  line
  line `(5) Wherever necessary, and particularly, in the case of subjects which do not fall within the`
  line `competence of any of the Scientific Panel, the Scientific Committee shall set up working groups and in`
  line `such cases, it shall draw on the expertise of those working groups when establishing scientific opinions.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (5764)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Procedure for Scientific Committee and Scientific Panel.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5764&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The members of the Scientific`
  line `Committee, who are not members of the Scientific Panel and the members of the Scientific Panel shall be`
  line `appointed by the Food Authority, for a period of three years, which shall be renewable for such period,`
  line `and the vacancy notice shall be published in the relevant leading scientific publications and on the Food`
  line `Authoritys website for a call for expressions of interest.`
  line
  line `(2) The Scientific Committee and the Scientific Panel shall each choose a Chairperson from amongst`
  line `their members.`
  line
  line `(3) The Scientific Committee and the Scientific Panel shall act by a majority of their members and the`
  line `views of the members shall be recorded.`
  line
  line `(4) The procedure for the operation and co-operation of the Scientific Committee and the Scientific`
  line `Panel shall be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(5) These procedures shall relate in particular to--`
  line
  line `(a) The number of times that a member can serve consecutively on a Scientific Committee or`
  line `Scientific Panel;`
  line
  line `(b) the number of members in each Scientific Panel;`
  line
  line `(c) the procedure for re-imbursing the expenses of members of the Scientific Committee and the`
  line `Scientific Panel;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner in which tasks and requests for scientific opinions are assigned to the Scientific`
  line `Committee and the Scientific Panel;`
  line
  line `(e) The creation and organisation of the working groups of the Scientific Committee and the`
  line `Scientific Panel, and the possibility of external experts being included in those working groups;`
  line
  line `(f) The possibility of observers being invited to meetings of the Scientific Committee and the`
  line `Scientific Panel;`
  line
  line `(g) The possibility of organising public hearings; and`
  line
  line `(h) Quorum of the meeting, meeting notice, agenda of the meeting and such other matters.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (5765)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Duties and functions of Food Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5765&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of the Food Authority to`
  line `regulate and monitor the manufacture, processing, distribution, sale and import of food so as to ensure`
  line `safe and wholesome food.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Food Authority may by regulations`
  line specify--
  line
  line `(a) the standards and guidelines in relation to articles of food and specifying an appropriate`
  line `system for enforcing various standards notified under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) the limits for use of food additives, crop contaminants, pesticide residues, residues of`
  line `veterinary drugs, heavy metals, processing aids, myco-toxins, antibiotics and pharmacological active`
  line `substances and irradiation of food;`
  line
  line `(c) the mechanisms and guidelines for accreditation of certification bodies engaged in`
  line `certification of food safety management systems for food businesses;`
  line
  line `(d) the procedure and the enforcement of quality control in relation to any article of food`
  line `imported into India;`
  line
  line `(e) the procedure and guidelines for accreditation of laboratories and notification of the accredited`
  line laboratories;
  line
  line `(f) the method of sampling, analysis and exchange of information among enforcement authorities;`
  line
  line `(g) conduct survey of enforcement and administration of this Act in the country;`
  line
  line `(h) food labelling standards including claims on health, nutrition, special dietary uses and food`
  line `category systems for foods; and`
  line
  line `(i) the manner in which and the procedure subject to which risk analysis, risk assessment, risk`
  line `communication and risk management shall be undertaken.`
  line
  line `(3) The Food Authority shall also--`
  line
  line `(a) provide scientific advice and technical support to the Central Government and the State`
  line `Governments in matters of framing the policy and rules in areas which have a direct or indirect`
  line `bearing on food safety and nutrition;`
  line
  line `(b) search, collect, collate, analyse and summarise relevant scientific and technical data`
  line `particularly relating to--`
  line
  line `(i) food consumption and the exposure of individuals to risks related to the consumption of`
  line food;
  line
  line `(ii) incidence and prevalence of biological risk;`
  line
  line `(iii) contaminants in food;`
  line
  line `(iv) residues of various contaminants;`
  line
  line `(v) identification of emerging risks; and`
  line
  line `(vi) introduction of rapid alert system;`
  line
  line `(c) promote, co-ordinate and issue guidelines for the development of risk assessment`
  line `methodologies and monitor and conduct and forward messages on the health and nutritional risks of`
  line `food to the Central Government, State Governments and Commissioners of Food Safety;`
  line
  line `(d) provide scientific and technical advice and assistance to the Central Government and the State`
  line `Governments in implementation of crisis management procedures with regard to food safety and to`
  line `draw up a general plan for crisis management and work in close co-operation with the crisis unit set`
  line `up by the Central Government in this regard;`
  line
  line `(e) establish a system of network of organisations with the aim to facilitate a scientific cooperation`
  line `framework by the co-ordination of activities, the exchange of information, the development`
  line `and implementation of joint projects, the exchange of expertise and best practices in the fields within`
  line `the Food Authoritys responsibility;`
  line
  line `(f) provide scientific and technical assistance to the Central Government and the State`
  line `Governments for improving co-operation with international organisations;`
  line
  line `(g) take all such steps to ensure that the public, consumers, interested parties and all levels of`
  line `panchayats receive rapid, reliable, objective and comprehensive information through appropriate`
  line `methods and means;`
  line
  line `(h) provide, whether within or outside their area, training programmes in food safety and`
  line `standards for persons who are or intend to become involved in food businesses, whether as food`
  line `business operators or employees or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(i) undertake any other task assigned to it by the Central Government to carry out the objects of`
  line `this Act;`
  line
  line `(j) contribute to the development of international technical standards for food, sanitary and phytosanitary`
  line standards;
  line
  line `(k) contribute, where relevant and appropriate to the development of agreement on recognition of`
  line `the equivalence of specific food related measures;`
  line
  line `(l) promote co-ordination of work on food standards undertaken by international governmental`
  line `and non-governmental organisations;`
  line
  line `(m) promote consistency between international technical standards and domestic food standards`
  line `while ensuring that the level of protection adopted in the country is not reduced; and`
  line
  line `(n) promote general awareness as to food safety and food standards.`
  line
  line `(4) The Food Authority shall make it public without undue delay--`
  line
  line `(a) the opinions of the Scientific Committee and the Scientific Panel immediately after adoption;`
  line
  line `(b) the annual declarations of interest made by members of the Food Authority, the Chief`
  line `Executive Officer, members of the Advisory Committee and members of the Scientific Committee`
  line `and Scientific Panel, as well as the declarations of interest if any, made in relation to items on the`
  line `agendas of meetings;`
  line
  line `(c) the results of its scientific studies; and`
  line
  line `(d) the annual report of its activities.`
  line
  line `(5) The Food Authority may, from time to time give such directions, on matters relating to food safety`
  line `and standards, to the Commissioner of Food Safety, who shall be bound by such directions while`
  line `exercising his powers under this Act.`
  line
  line `(6) The Food Authority shall not disclose or cause to be disclosed to third parties confidential`
  line `information that it receives for which confidential treatment has been requested and has been acceded,`
  line `except for information which must be made public if circumstances so require, in order to protect public`
  line health.
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (5766)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Proceedings of Food Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5766&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Food Authority shall meet at the head office or any of`
  line `its offices at such time as the Chairperson may direct, and shall observe such rules of procedure in regard`
  line `to the transaction of business at its meetings (including the quorum at its meetings) as may be specified by`
  line regulations.
  line
  line `(2) If the Chairperson is unable to attend a meeting of the Food Authority, any other Member`
  line `nominated by the Chairperson in this behalf and, in the absence of such nomination or where there is no`
  line `Chairperson, any Member chosen by the Members present from amongst themselves, shall preside at the`
  line meeting.
  line
  line `(3) All questions which come up before any meeting of the Food Authority shall be decided by a`
  line `majority of votes of the Members present and voting, and in the event of an equality of votes, the`
  line `Chairperson or the person presiding over the meeting shall have the right to exercise a second or casting`
  line vote.
  line
  line `(4) All orders and decisions of the Food Authority shall be authenticated by the Chief Executive`
  line Officer.
  line
  line `(5) The Chief Executive Officer shall take part in the meetings of the Food Authority but without a`
  line `right to vote.`
  line
  line `(6) The Food Authority may invite the Chairperson of the Scientific Committee to attend its meetings`
  line `but without a right to vote.`
  line
  line `(7) No act or proceedings of the Food Authority shall be questioned or invalidated merely on the`
  line `ground of existence of any vacancy or defect in the constitution of Food Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (5767)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `General principles to be followed in administration of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5767&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government, the State`
  line `Governments, the Food Authority and other agencies, as the case may be, while implementing the`
  line `provisions of this Act shall be guided by the following principles namely:--`
  line
  line `(1) (a) endeavour to achieve an appropriate level of protection of human life and health and the`
  line `protection of consumers interests, including fair practices in all kinds of food trade with reference to`
  line `food safety standards and practices;`
  line
  line `(b) carry out risk management which shall include taking into account the results of risk`
  line `assessment and other factors which in the opinion of the Food Authority are relevant to the matter`
  line `under consideration and where the conditions are relevant, in order to achieve the general objectives`
  line `of regulations;`
  line
  line `(c) where in any specific circumstances, on the basis of assessment of available information, the`
  line `possibility of harmful effects on health is identified but scientific uncertainty persists, provisional risk`
  line `management measures necessary to ensure appropriate level of health protection may be adopted,`
  line `pending further scientific information for a more comprehensive risk assessment;`
  line
  line `(d) the measures adopted on the basis of clause (c) shall be proportionate and no more restrictive`
  line `of trade than is required to achieve appropriate level of health protection, regard being had to`
  line `technical and economic feasibility and other factors regarded as reasonable and proper in the matter`
  line `under consideration;`
  line
  line `(e) the measures adopted shall be reviewed within a reasonable period of time, depending on the`
  line `nature of the risk to life or health being identified and the type of scientific information needed to`
  line `clarify the scientific uncertainty and to conduct a more comprehensive risk assessment;`
  line
  line `(f) in cases where there are reasonable grounds to suspect that a food may present a risk for`
  line `human health, then, depending on the nature, seriousness and extent of that risk, the Food Authority`
  line `and the Commissioner of Food Safety shall take appropriate steps to inform the general public of the`
  line `nature of the risk to health, identifying to the fullest extent possible the food or type of food, the risk`
  line `that it may present, and the measures which are taken or about to be taken to prevent, reduce or`
  line `eliminate that risk; and`
  line
  line `(g) where any food which fails to comply with food safety requirements is part of a batch, lot or`
  line `consignment of food of the same class or description, it shall be presumed until the contrary is`
  line `proved, that all of the food in that batch, lot or consignment fails to comply with those requirements.`
  line
  line `(2) The Food Authority shall, while framing regulations or specifying standards under this Act--`
  line
  line `(a) take into account--`
  line
  line `(i) prevalent practices and conditions in the country including agricultural practices and`
  line `handling, storage and transport conditions; and`
  line
  line `(ii) international standards and practices, where international standards or practices exist`
  line `or are in the process of being formulated,`
  line `unless it is of opinion that taking into account of such prevalent practices and conditions or`
  line `international standards or practices or any particular part thereof would not be an effective or`
  line `appropriate means for securing the objectives of such regulations or where there is a scientific`
  line `justification or where they would result in a different level of protection from the one determined as`
  line `appropriate in the country;`
  line
  line `(b) determine food standards on the basis of risk analysis except where it is of opinion that`
  line `such analysis is not appropriate to the circumstances or the nature of the case;`
  line
  line `(c) undertake risk assessment based on the available scientific evidence and in an`
  line `independent, objective and transparent manner;`
  line
  line `(d) ensure that there is open and transparent public consultation, directly or through`
  line `representative bodies including all levels of panchayats, during the preparation, evaluation and`
  line `revision of regulations, except where it is of opinion that there is an urgency concerning food`
  line `safety or public health to make or amend the regulations in which case such consultation may be`
  line `dispensed with:`
  line
  line `Provided that such regulations shall be in force for not more than six months;`
  line
  line `(e) ensure protection of the interests of consumers and shall provide a basis for consumers to`
  line `make informed choices in relation to the foods they consume;`
  line
  line `(f) ensure prevention of--`
  line
  line `(i) fraudulent, deceptive or unfair trade practices which may mislead or harm the`
  line `consumer; and`
  line
  line `(ii) unsafe or contaminated or sub-standard food.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of this Act shall not apply to any farmer or fisherman or farming operations or`
  line `crops or livestock or aquaculture, and supplies used or produced in farming or products of crops`
  line `produced by a farmer at farm level or a fisherman in his operations.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (5768)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Use of food additive or processing aid.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5768&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `No article of food shall contain any food additive or`
  line `processing aid unless it is in accordance with the provisions of this Act and regulations made thereunder.`
  line
  line `Explanation. - For the purposes of this section, "processing aid" means any substance or material, not`
  line `including apparatus or utensils, and not consumed as a food ingredient by itself, used in the processing of`
  line `raw materials, foods or its ingredients to fulfil a certain technological purpose during treatment or`
  line `processing and which may result in the non-intentional but unavoidable presence of residues or`
  line `derivatives in the final product.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (5769)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Contaminants, naturally occurring toxic substances, heavy metals, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5769&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `No article of food`
  line `shall contain any contaminant, naturally occurring toxic substances or toxins or hormone or heavy metals`
  line `in excess of such quantities as may be specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (5770)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Pesticides, veterinary drugs residues, antibiotic residues and microbiological counts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5770&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) No`
  line `article of food shall contain insecticides or pesticides residues, veterinary drugs residues, antibiotic`
  line `residues, solvent residues, pharmacological active substances and micro-biological counts in excess of`
  line `such tolerance limit as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) No insecticide shall be used directly on article of food except fumigants registered and approved`
  line `under the Insecticides Act, 1968 (46 of 1968).`
  line
  line `Explanation. - For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(1) "pesticide residue" means any specified substance in food resulting from the use of a pesticide`
  line `and includes any derivatives of a pesticide, such as conversion products, metabolites, reaction`
  line `products and impurities considered to be of toxicological significance and also includes such residues`
  line `coming into food from environment;`
  line
  line `(2) "residues of veterinary drugs" include the parent compounds or their metabolites or both in`
  line `any edible portion of any animal product and include residues of associated impurities of the`
  line `veterinary drugs concerned.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (5771)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Genetically modified foods, organic foods, functional foods, proprietary foods, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5771&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Save as`
  line `otherwise provided under this Act and regulations made thereunder, no person shall manufacture,`
  line `distribute, sell or import any novel food, genetically modified articles of food, irradiated food, organic`
  line `foods, foods for special dietary uses, functional foods, neutraceuticals, health supplements, proprietary`
  line `foods and such other articles of food which the Central Government may notify in this behalf.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(1) "foods for special dietary uses or functional foods or nutraceuticals or health supplements" means:`
  line
  line `(a) foods which are specially processed or formulated to satisfy particular dietary requirements`
  line `which exist because of a particular physical or physiological condition or specific diseases and`
  line `disorders and which are presented as such, wherein the composition of these foodstuffs must differ`
  line `significantly from the composition of ordinary foods of comparable nature, if such ordinary foods`
  line `exist, and may contain one or more of the following ingredients, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) plants or botanicals or their parts in the form of powder, concentrate or extract in water,`
  line `ethyl alcohol or hydro alcoholic extract, single or in combination;`
  line
  line `(ii) minerals or vitamins or proteins or metals or their compounds or amino acids (in amounts`
  line `not exceeding the Recommended Daily Allowance for Indians) or enzymes (within permissible`
  line `limits);`
  line
  line `(iii) substances from animal origin;`
  line
  line `(iv) a dietary substance for use by human beings to supplement the diet by increasing the total`
  line `dietary intake;`
  line
  line `(b) (i) a product that is labelled as a "Food for special dietary uses or functional foods or`
  line `nutraceuticals or health supplements or similar such foods" which is not represented for use as a`
  line `conventional food and whereby such products may be formulated in the form of powders, granules,`
  line `tablets, capsules, liquids, jelly and other dosage forms but not parenterals, and are meant for oral`
  line administration;
  line
  line `(ii) such product does not include a drug as defined in clause (b) and ayurvedic, sidha and unani`
  line `drugs as defined in clauses (a) and (h) of section 3 of the Drugs and Cosmetics Act, 1940 (23 of`
  line `1940) and rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(iii) does not claim to cure or mitigate any specific disease, disorder or condition (except for`
  line `certain health benefit or such promotion claims) as may be permitted by the regulations made under`
  line `this Act;`
  line
  line `(iv) does not include a narcotic drug or a psychotropic substance as defined in the Schedule of the`
  line `Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances Act, 1985 (61 of 1985) and rules made thereunder and`
  line `substances listed in Schedules E and EI of the Drugs and Cosmetics Rules, 1945;`
  line
  line `(2) "genetically engineered or modified food" means food and food ingredients composed of or`
  line `containing genetically modified or engineered organisms obtained through modern biotechnology, or food`
  line `and food ingredients produced from but not containing genetically modified or engineered organisms`
  line `obtained through modern biotechnology;`
  line
  line `(3) "organic food" means food products that have been produced in accordance with specified organic`
  line `production standards;`
  line
  line `(4) "proprietary and novel food" means an article of food for which standards have not been specified`
  line `but is not unsafe:`
  line
  line `Provided that such food does not contain any of the foods and ingredients prohibited under this Act`
  line `and the regulations made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (5772)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Packaging and labelling of foods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5772&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall manufacture, distribute, sell or expose for`
  line `sale or despatch or deliver to any agent or broker for the purpose of sale, any packaged food products`
  line `which are not marked and labelled in the manner as may be specified by regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided that the labels shall not contain any statement, claim, design or device which is false or`
  line `misleading in any particular concerning the food products contained in the package or concerning the`
  line `quantity or the nutritive value implying medicinal or therapeutic claims or in relation to the place of`
  line `origin of the said food products.`
  line
  line `(2) Every food business operator shall ensure that the labelling and presentation of food, including`
  line `their shape, appearance or packaging, the packaging materials used, the manner in which they are`
  line `arranged and the setting in which they are displayed, and the information which is made available about`
  line `them through whatever medium, does not mislead consumers.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (5773)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Restrictions of advertisement and prohibition as to unfair trade practices.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5773&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `No advertisement`
  line `shall be made of any food which is misleading or deceiving or contravenes the provisions of this Act, the`
  line `rules and regulations made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) No person shall engage himself in any unfair trade practice for purpose of promoting the sale,`
  line `supply, use and consumption of articles of food or adopt any unfair or deceptive practice including the`
  line `practice of making any statement, whether orally or in writing or by visible representation which--`
  line
  line `(a) falsely represents that the foods are of a particular standard, quality, quantity or gradecomposition;`
  line
  line `(b) makes a false or misleading representation concerning the need for, or the usefulness;`
  line
  line `(c) gives to the public any guarantee of the efficacy that is not based on an adequate or scientific`
  line `justification thereof:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a defence is raised to the effect that such guarantee is based on adequate or`
  line `scientific justification, the burden of proof of such defence shall lie on the person raising such`
  line defence.
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (5774)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `All imports of articles of food to be subject to this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5774&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `No person shall import into India--`
  line
  line `(i) any unsafe or misbranded or sub-standard food or food containing extraneous matter;`
  line
  line `(ii) any article of food for the import of which a licence is required under any Act or rules or`
  line `regulations, except in accordance with the conditions of the licence; and`
  line
  line `(iii) any article of food in contravention of any other provision of this Act or of any rule or`
  line `regulation made thereunder or any other Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall, while prohibiting, restricting or otherwise regulating import of`
  line `article of food under the Foreign Trade (Development and Regulation) Act, 1992 (22 of 1992), follow the`
  line `standards laid down by the Food Authority under the provisions of this Act and the Rules and regulations`
  line `made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (5775)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Responsibilities of the food business operator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5775&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every food business operator shall ensure`
  line `that the articles of food satisfy the requirements of this Act and the rules and regulations made thereunder`
  line `at all stages of production, processing, import, distribution and sale within the businesses under his`
  line control.
  line
  line `(2) No food business operator shall himself or by any person on his behalf manufacture, store, sell or`
  line `distribute any article of food--`
  line
  line `(i) which is unsafe; or`
  line
  line `(ii) which is misbranded or sub-standard or contains extraneous matter; or`
  line
  line `(iii) for which a licence is required, except in accordance with the conditions of the licence; or`
  line
  line `(iv) which is for the time being prohibited by the Food Authority or the Central Government or`
  line `the State Government in the interest of public health; or`
  line
  line `(v) in contravention of any other provision of this Act or of any rule or regulation made`
  line thereunder.
  line
  line `(3) No food business operator shall employ any person who is suffering from infectious, contagious`
  line `or loathsome disease.`
  line
  line `(4) No food business operator shall sell or offer for sale any article of food to any vendor unless he`
  line `also gives a guarantee in writing in the form specified by regulations about the nature and quality of such`
  line `article to the vendor:`
  line
  line `Provided that a bill, cash memo, or invoice in respect of the sale of any article of food given by a food`
  line `business operator to the vendor shall be deemed to be a guarantee under this section, even if a guarantee`
  line `in the specified form is not included in the bill, cash memo or invoice.`
  line
  line `(5) Where any food which is unsafe is part of a batch, lot or consignment of food of the same class or`
  line `description, it shall be presumed that all the food in that batch, lot or consignment is also unsafe, unless`
  line `following a detailed assessment within a specified time, it is found that there is no evidence that the rest`
  line `of the batch, lot or consignment is unsafe:`
  line
  line `Provided that any conformity of a food with specific provisions applicable to that food shall be`
  line `without prejudice to the competent authorities taking appropriate measures to impose restrictions on that`
  line `food being placed on the market or to require its withdrawal from the market for the reasons to be`
  line `recorded in writing where such authorities suspect that, despite the conformity, the food is unsafe.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (5776)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Liability of the manufacturers, packers, wholesalers, distributors and sellers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5776&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `manufacturer or packer of an article of food shall be liable for such article of food if it does not meet the`
  line `requirements of this Act and the rules and regulations made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) The wholesaler or distributor shall be liable under this Act for any article of food which is--`
  line
  line `(a) supplied after the date of its expiry; or`
  line
  line `(b) stored or supplied in violation of the safety instructions of the manufacturer; or`
  line
  line `(c) unsafe or misbranded; or`
  line
  line `(d) unidentifiable of manufacturer from whom the article of food have been received; or`
  line
  line `(e) stored or handled or kept in violation of the provisions of this Act, the rules and regulations`
  line `made thereunder; or`
  line
  line `(f) received by him with knowledge of being unsafe.`
  line
  line `(3) The seller shall be liable under this Act for any article of food which is--`
  line
  line `(a) sold after the date of its expiry; or`
  line
  line `(b) handled or kept in unhygienic conditions; or`
  line
  line `(c) misbranded; or`
  line
  line `(d) unidentifiable of the manufacturer or the distributors from whom such articles of food were`
  line `received; or`
  line
  line `(e) received by him with knowledge of being unsafe.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (5777)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Food recall procedures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5777&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a food business operator considers or has reasons to believe that a`
  line `food which he has processed, manufactured or distributed is not in compliance with this Act, or the rules`
  line `or regulations, made thereunder, he shall immediately initiate procedures to withdraw the food in question`
  line `from the market and consumers indicating reasons for its withdrawal and inform the competent authorities`
  line thereof.
  line
  line `(2) A food business operator shall immediately inform the competent authorities and co-operate with`
  line `them, if he considers or has reasons to believe that a food which he has placed on the market may be`
  line `unsafe for the consumers.`
  line
  line `(3) The food business operator shall inform the competent authorities of the action taken to prevent`
  line `risks to the consumer and shall not prevent or discourage any person from co-operating, in accordance`
  line `with this Act, with the competent authorities, where this may prevent, reduce or eliminate a risk arising`
  line `from a food.`
  line
  line `(4) Every food business operator shall follow such conditions and guidelines relating to food recall`
  line `procedures as the Food Authority may specify by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (5778)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Authorities responsible for enforcement of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5778&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Food Authority and the State Food`
  line `Safety Authorities shall be responsible for the enforcement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Food Authority and the State Food Safety Authorities shall monitor and verify that the`
  line `relevant requirements of law are fulfilled by food business operators at all stages of food business.`
  line
  line `(3) The authorities shall maintain a system of control and other activities as appropriate to the`
  line `circumstances, including public communication on food safety and risk, food safety surveillance and`
  line `other monitoring activities covering all stages of food business.`
  line
  line `(4) The Food Safety Officers shall enforce and execute within their area the provisions of this Act`
  line `with respect to which the duty is not imposed expressly or by necessary implication on some other`
  line authority.
  line
  line `(5) The regulations under this Act shall specify which of the Food Safety Officers are to enforce and`
  line `execute them, either generally or in relation to cases of a particular description or a particular area, and`
  line `any such regulations or orders may provide for the giving of assistance and information by any authority`
  line `concerned in 11the administration of the regulations or orders, or of any provisions of this Act, to any`
  line `other authority so concerned, for the purposes of their respective duties under them.`
  line
  line `(6) The Commissioner of Food Safety and Designated Officer shall exercise the same powers as are`
  line `conferred on the Food Safety Officer and follow the same procedure specified in this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (5779)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Commissioner of Food Safety of the State.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5779&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall appoint the`
  line `Commissioner of Food Safety for the State for efficient implementation of food safety and standards and`
  line `other requirements laid down under this Act and the rules and regulations made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner of Food Safety shall perform all or any of the following functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) prohibit in the interest of public health, the manufacture, storage, distribution or sale of any`
  line `article of food, either in the whole of the State or any area or part thereof for such period, not`
  line `exceeding one year, as may be specified in the order notified in this behalf in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(b) carry out survey of the industrial units engaged in the manufacture or processing of food in`
  line `the State to find out compliance by such units of the standards notified by the Food Authority for`
  line `various articles of food;`
  line
  line `(c) conduct or organise training programmes for the personnel of the office of the Commissioner`
  line `of Food Safety and, on a wider scale, for different segments of food chain for generating awareness`
  line `on food safety;`
  line
  line `(d) ensure an efficient and uniform implementation of the standards and other requirements as`
  line `specified and also ensure a high standard of objectivity, accountability, practicability, transparency`
  line `and credibility;`
  line
  line `(e) sanction prosecution for offences punishable with imprisonment under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) such other functions as the State Government may, in consultation with the Food Authority,`
  line prescribe.
  line
  line `(3) The Commissioner of Food Safety may, by Order, delegate, subject to such conditions and`
  line `restrictions as may be specified in the Order, such of his powers and functions under this Act (except the`
  line `power to appoint Designated Officer, Food Safety Officer and Food Analyst) as he may deem necessary`
  line `or expedient to any officer subordinate to him.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (5780)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Licensing and registration of food business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5780&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall commence or carry on any`
  line `food business except under a licence.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall apply to a petty manufacturer who himself`
  line `manufactures or sells any article of food or a petty retailer, hawker, itinerant vendor or a temporary stall`
  line `holder or small scale or cottage or such other industries relating to food business or tiny food business`
  line `operator; but they shall register themselves with such authority and in such manner as may be specified`
  line `by regulations, without prejudice to the availability of safe and wholesome food for human consumption`
  line `or affecting the interests of the consumers.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person desirous to commence or carry on any food business shall make an application for`
  line `grant of a licence to the Designated Officer in such manner containing such particulars and fees as may be`
  line `specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(4) The Designated Officer on receipt of an application under sub-section (3), may either grant the`
  line `licence or after giving the applicant an opportunity of being heard and for reasons to be recorded in`
  line `writing, refuse to grant a licence to any applicant, if he is satisfied that it is necessary so to do in the`
  line `interest of public health and shall make available to the applicant a copy of the order:`
  line
  line `Provided that if a licence is not issued within two months from the date of making the application or`
  line `his application is not rejected, the applicant may start his food business after expiry of the said period and`
  line `in such a case, the Designated Officer shall not refuse to issue a licence but may, if he considers`
  line `necessary, issue an improvement notice, under section 32 and follow procedures in that regard.`
  line
  line `(5) Every licence shall be in such form and subject to such conditions as may be specified by`
  line regulations.
  line
  line `(6) A single licence may be issued by the Designated Officer for one or more articles of food and also`
  line `for different establishments or premises in the same area.`
  line
  line `(7) If the articles of food are manufactured, stored, sold or exhibited for sale at different premises`
  line `situated in more than one area, separate applications shall be made and separate licence shall be issued in`
  line `respect of such premises not falling within the same area.`
  line
  line `(8) An appeal against the order of rejection for the grant of licence shall lie to the Commissioner of`
  line `Food Safety.`
  line
  line `(9) A licence unless suspended or cancelled earlier shall be in force for such period as may be`
  line `specified by regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided that if an application for a renewal of licence is made before the expiry of the period of`
  line `validity of the licence, the licence shall continue to be in force until orders are passed on the application.`
  line
  line `(10) The licence shall subsist for the benefit of the deceased's personal representative or any other`
  line `member of his family, until the expiry of--`
  line
  line `(a) the period of three months beginning with his death; or`
  line
  line `(b) such longer period as the Designated Officer may allow.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (5781)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Improvement notices.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5781&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Designated Officer has reasonable ground for believing that any`
  line `food business operator has failed to comply with any regulations to which this section applies, he may, by`
  line `a notice served on that food business operator (in this Act referred to as an "improvement notice")--`
  line
  line `(a) state the grounds for believing that the food business operator has failed to comply with the`
  line regulations;
  line
  line `(b) specify the matters which constitute the food business operator"s failure so to comply;`
  line
  line `(c) specify the measures which, in the opinion of the said Authority, the food business operator`
  line `must take, in order to secure compliance; and`
  line
  line `(d) require the food business operator to take those measures, or measures which are at least`
  line `equivalent to them, within a reasonable period (not being less than fourteen days) as may be specified`
  line `in the notice.`
  line
  line `(2) If the food business operator fails to comply with an improvement notice, his licence may be`
  line suspended.
  line
  line `(3) If the food business operator still fails to comply with the improvement notice, the Designated`
  line `Officer may, after giving the licensee an opportunity to show cause, cancel the licence granted to him:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Designated Officer may suspend any licence forthwith in the interest of public`
  line `health for reasons to be recorded in writing.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person who is aggrieved by--`
  line
  line `(a) an improvement notice; or`
  line
  line `(b) refusal to issue a certificate as to improvement; or`
  line
  line `(c) cancellation or suspension or revocation of licence under this Act,`
  line
  line `may appeal to the Commissioner of Food Safety whose decision thereon, shall be final.`
  line
  line `(5) The period within which such an appeal may be brought shall be--`
  line
  line `(a) fifteen days from the date on which notice of the decision was served on the person desiring to`
  line `appeal; or`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of an appeal under sub-section (1), the said period or the period specified in the`
  line `improvement notice, whichever expires earlier.`
  line
  line `Explanation--For the purpose of this sub-section, the making of the complaint shall be deemed to`
  line `be the bringing of the appeal.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (5782)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Prohibition orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5782&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) If--`
  line
  line `(a) any food business operator is convicted of an offence under this Act; and`
  line
  line `(b) the court by or before which he is so convicted is satisfied that the health risk exists with`
  line `respect to that food business,`
  line
  line `the court, after giving the food business operator an opportunity of being heard, may by an order, impose`
  line `the following prohibitions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) a prohibition on the use of the process or treatment for the purposes of the food business;`
  line
  line `(ii) a prohibition on the use of the premises or equipment for the purposes of the food business or`
  line `any other food business of the same class or description;`
  line
  line `(iii) a prohibition on the use of the premises or equipment for the purposes of any food business.`
  line
  line `(2) The court may, on being satisfied that it is necessary so to do, by an order, impose a prohibition on`
  line `the food business operator participating in the management of any food business, or any food business of`
  line `a class or description specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(3) As soon as practicable after the making of an order under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) (in`
  line `this Act referred to as a "prohibition order"), the concerned Food Safety Officer shall--`
  line
  line `(a) serve a copy of the order on the food business operator; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of an order under sub-section (1), affix a copy of the order at a conspicuous place`
  line `on such premises used for the purposes of the food business,`
  line
  line `and any person who knowingly contravenes such an order shall be guilty of an offence and be punishable`
  line `with a fine which may extend to three lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(4) The concerned Food Safety Officer shall with the approval of the Designated Officer issue a`
  line `certificate to the effect that the food business operator has taken sufficient measures justifying lifting of`
  line `the prohibition order, within seven days of his being satisfied on an application made by the food business`
  line `operator for such a certificate or the said officer shall--`
  line
  line `(a) determine, as soon as is reasonably practicable and in any event within fourteen days, whether`
  line `or not he is so satisfied; and`
  line
  line `(b) if he determines that he is not so satisfied, give notice to the food business operator of the`
  line `reasons for that determination.`
  line
  line `(5) A prohibition order shall cease to have effect upon the court being satisfied, on an application`
  line `made by the food business operator not less than six months after the prohibition order has been passed,`
  line `that the food business operator has taken sufficient measures justifying the lifting of the prohibition order.`
  line
  line `(6) The court shall give a direction on an application by the food business operator, if the court thinks`
  line `it proper so to do having regard to all the circumstances of the case, including in particular, the conduct of`
  line `the food business operator since the making of the order; but no such application shall be entertained if it`
  line `is not made--`
  line
  line `(a) within six months after the making of the prohibition order; or`
  line
  line `(b) within three months after the making by the food business operator of a previous application`
  line `for such a direction.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this section,--`
  line
  line `(i) any reference above shall apply in relation to a manager of a food business as it applies in`
  line `relation to the food business operator; and any reference to the food business operator of the business,`
  line `or to the food business operator, shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(ii) "manager", in relation to a food business, means any person who is entrusted by the food`
  line `business operator with the day-to-day running of the business, or any part of the business.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (5783)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Emergency prohibition notices and orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5783&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Designated Officer is satisfied that the`
  line `health risk condition exists with respect to any food business, he may, after a notice served on the food`
  line `business operator (in this Act referred to as an "emergency prohibition notice"), apply to the`
  line `Commissioner of Food Safety for imposing the prohibition.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Commissioner of Food Safety is satisfied, on the application of such an officer, that the`
  line `health risk condition exists with respect to any food business, he shall, by an order, impose the`
  line prohibition.
  line
  line `(3) The Designated Officer shall not apply for an emergency prohibition order unless, at least one day`
  line `before the date of the application, he has served notice on the food business operator of the business of his`
  line `intention to apply for the order.`
  line
  line `(4) As soon as practicable after the making of an emergency prohibition order, the Designated Officer`
  line `shall require the Food Safety Officer to--`
  line
  line `(a) serve a copy of the order on the food business operator of the business; or`
  line
  line `(b) affix a copy of the order at a conspicuous place on such premises used for the purposes of that`
  line business;
  line
  line `and any person who knowingly contravenes such an order shall be guilty of an offence and shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years and with fine which may extend`
  line `to two lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(5) An emergency prohibition order shall cease to have effect on the issue by the Designated Officer`
  line `of a certificate to the effect that he is satisfied that the food business operator has taken sufficient`
  line `measures for justifying the lifting of such order.`
  line
  line `(6) The Designated Officer shall issue a certificate under sub-section (5) within seven days of an`
  line `application by the food business operator for such a certificate and on his being not satisfied, the said`
  line `officer shall give notice to the food business operator within a period of ten days indicating the reasons`
  line `for such decision.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (5784)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Notification of food poisoning.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5784&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `The Food Authority may, by notification, require registered`
  line `medical practitioners carrying on their profession in any local area specified in the notification, to report`
  line `all occurrences of food poisoning coming to their notice to such officer as may be specified.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (5785)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Designated Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5785&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner of Food Safety shall, by order, appoint the Designated`
  line `Officer, who shall not be below the rank of a Sub-Divisional Officer, to be in-charge of food safety`
  line `administration in such area as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) There shall be a Designated Officer for each district.`
  line
  line `(3) The functions to be performed by the Designated Officer shall be as follows, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) to issue or cancel licence of food business operators;`
  line
  line `(b) to prohibit the sale of any article of food which is in contravention of the provisions of this`
  line `Act and rules and regulations made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(c) to receive report and samples of article of foods from Food Safety Officer under his`
  line `jurisdiction and get them analysed;`
  line
  line `(d) to make recommendations to the Commissioner of Food Safety for sanction to launch`
  line `prosecutions in case of contraventions punishable with imprisonment;`
  line
  line `(e) to sanction or launch prosecutions in cases of contraventions punishable with fine;`
  line
  line `(f) to maintain record of all inspections made by Food Safety Officers and action taken by them in`
  line `the performance of their duties;`
  line
  line `(g) to get investigated any complaint which may be made in writing in respect of any`
  line `contravention of the provisions of this Act and the rules and regulations made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(h) to investigate any complaint which may be made in writing against the Food Safety Officer;`
  line and
  line
  line `(i) to perform such other duties as may be entrusted by the Commissioner of Food Safety.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (5786)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Food Safety Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5786&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner of Food Safety shall, by notification, appoint such`
  line `persons as he thinks fit, having the qualifications prescribed by the Central Government, as Food Safety`
  line `Officers for such local areas as he may assign to them for the purpose of performing functions under this`
  line `Act and the rules and regulations made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may authorise any officer of the State Government having the`
  line `qualifications prescribed under sub-section (1) to perform the functions of a Food Safety Officer within a`
  line `specified jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (5787)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Powers of Food Safety Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5787&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Food Safety Officer may--`
  line
  line `(a) take a sample--`
  line
  line `(i) of any food, or any substance, which appears to him to be intended for sale, or to have`
  line `been sold for human consumption; or`
  line
  line `(ii) of any article of food or substance which is found by him on or in any such premises;`
  line
  line `which he has reason to believe that it may be required as evidence in proceedings under any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act or of the regulations or orders made thereunder; or`
  line
  line `(b) seize any article of food which appears to the Food Safety Officer to be in contravention of`
  line `this Act or the regulations made thereunder; and`
  line
  line `(c) keep it in the safe custody of the food business operator such article of food after taking a`
  line sample;
  line
  line `and in both cases send the same for analysis to a Food Analyst for the local area within which such`
  line `sample has been taken:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Food Safety Officer keeps such article in the safe custody of the food`
  line `business operator, he may require the food business operator to execute a bond for a sum of money equal`
  line `to the value of such article with one or more sureties as the Food Safety Officer deems fit and the food`
  line `business operator shall execute the bond accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) The Food Safety Officer may enter and inspect any place where the article of food is`
  line `manufactured, or stored for sale, or stored for the manufacture of any other article of food, or exposed or`
  line `exhibited for sale and where any adulterant is manufactured or kept, and take samples of such articles`
  line `of food or adulterant for analysis.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any sample is taken, its cost calculated at the rate at which the article is usually sold to the`
  line `public shall be paid to the person from whom it is taken.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any article of food seized under clause (b) of sub-ection (1) is of a perishable nature and`
  line `the Food Safety Officer is satisfied that such article of food is so deteriorated that it is unfit for human`
  line `consumption, the Food Safety Officer may, after giving notice in writing to the food business operator,`
  line `cause the same to be destroyed.`
  line
  line `(5) The Food Safety Officer shall, in exercising the powers of entry upon, and inspection of any place`
  line `under this section, follow, as far as may be, the provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of`
  line `1974) relating to the search or inspection of a place by a police officer executing a search warrant issued`
  line `under that Code.`
  line
  line `(6) Any adulterant found in the possession of a manufacturer or distributor of, or dealer in, any article`
  line `of food or in any of the premises occupied by him as such and for the possession of which he is unable to`
  line `account to the satisfaction of the Food Safety Officer and any books of account or other documents found`
  line `in his possession or control and which would be useful for, or relevant to, any investigation or proceeding`
  line `under this Act, may be seized by the Food Safety Officer and a sample of such adulterant submitted for`
  line `analysis to a Food Analyst:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such books of account or other documents shall be seized by the Food Safety Officer`
  line `except with the previous approval of the authority to which he is subordinate.`
  line
  line `(7) Where the Food Safety Officer takes any action under clause (a) of sub-section (1), or sub-section`
  line `(2), or sub-section (4) or sub-section (6), he shall, call one or more persons to be present at the time when`
  line `such action is taken and take his or their signatures.`
  line
  line `(8) Where any books of account or other documents are seized under sub-section (6), the Food Safety`
  line `Officer shall, within a period not exceeding thirty days from the date of seizure, return the same to the`
  line `person from whom they were seized after copies thereof or extracts there from as certified by that person`
  line `in such manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government have been taken:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such person refuses to so certify and a prosecution has been instituted against`
  line `him under this Act, such books of account or other documents shall be returned to him only after copies`
  line `thereof and extracts there from as certified by the court have been taken.`
  line
  line `(9) When any adulterant is seized under sub-section (6), the burden of proving that such adulterant is`
  line `not meant for purposes of adulteration shall be on the person from whose possession such adulterant was`
  line seized.
  line
  line `(10) The Commissioner of Food Safety may from time to time issue guidelines with regard to`
  line `exercise of powers of the Food Safety Officer, which shall be binding:`
  line
  line `Provided that the powers of such Food Safety Officer may also be revoked for a specified period by`
  line `the Commissioner of Food Safety.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (5788)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Liability of Food Safety Officer in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5788&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `Any Food Safety Officer exercising powers`
  line `under this Act or the rules and regulations made thereunder who--`
  line
  line `(a) vexatiously and without any reasonable ground seizes any article of food or adulterant; or`
  line
  line `(b) commits any other act to the injury of any person without having reason to believe that such`
  line `act is necessary for the execution of his duty,`
  line
  line `shall be guilty of an offence under this Act and shall be liable to a penalty which may extend to one lakh`
  line `rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case any false complaint is made against a Food Safety Officer and it is proved so,`
  line `the complainant shall be guilty of an offence under this Act and shall be punishable with fine which shall`
  line `not be less than fifty thousand rupees but may extend to one lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (5789)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Purchaser may have food analysed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5789&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing contained in this Act shall be held to prevent a`
  line `purchaser of any article of food other than a Food Safety Officer from having such article analysed by the`
  line `Food Analyst on payment of such fees and receiving from the Food Analyst a report of his analysis within`
  line `such period as may be specified by regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided that such purchaser shall inform the food business operator at the time of purchase of his`
  line `intention to have such article so analysed:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if the report of the Food Analyst shows that the article of food is not in`
  line `compliance with the Act or the rules or regulations made thereunder, the purchaser shall be entitled to get`
  line `refund of the fees paid by him under this section.`
  line
  line `(2) In case the Food Analyst finds the sample in contravention of the provisions of this Act and rules`
  line `and regulations made thereunder, the Food Analysts shall forward the report to the Designated Officer to`
  line `follow the procedure laid down in section 42 for prosecution.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (5790)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Power of search, seizure, investigation, prosecution and procedure thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5790&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2) of section 31, the Food Safety Officer may search`
  line `any place, seize any article of food or adulterant, if there is a reasonable doubt about them being involved`
  line `in commission of any offence relating to food, and shall thereafter inform the Designated Officer of the`
  line `actions taken by him in writing:`
  line
  line `Provided that no search shall be deemed to be irregular by reason only of the fact that witnesses for`
  line `the search are not inhabitants of the locality in which the place searched is situated.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as in this Act otherwise expressly provided, provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure,`
  line `1973 (2 of 1974) relating to search, seizure, summon, investigation and prosecution, shall apply, as far as`
  line `may be, to all action taken by the Food Safety Officer under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (5791)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Procedure for launching prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5791&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Food Safety Officer shall be responsible for`
  line `inspection of food business, drawing samples and sending them to Food Analyst for analysis.`
  line
  line `(2) The Food Analyst after receiving the sample from the Food Safety Officer shall analyse the`
  line `sample and send the analysis report mentioning method of sampling and analysis within fourteen days to`
  line `Designated Officer with a copy to Commissioner of Food Safety.`
  line
  line `(3) The Designated Officer after scrutiny of the report of Food Analyst shall decide as to whether the`
  line `contravention is punishable with imprisonment or fine only and in the case of contravention punishable`
  line `with imprisonment, he shall send his recommendations within fourteen days to the Commissioner of Food`
  line `Safety for sanctioning prosecution.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commissioner of Food Safety shall, if he so deems fit decide, within the period prescribed by`
  line `the Central Government, as per the gravity of offence, whether the matter be referred to,--`
  line
  line `(a) a court of ordinary jurisdiction in case of offences punishable with imprisonment for a term up`
  line `to three years; or`
  line
  line `(b) a Special Court in case of offences punishable with imprisonment for a term exceeding three`
  line `years where such Special Court is established and in case no Special Court is established, such cases`
  line `shall be tried by a Court of ordinary jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(5) The Commissioner of Food Safety shall communicate his decision to the Designated Officer and`
  line `the concerned Food Safety Officer who shall launch prosecution before courts of ordinary jurisdiction or`
  line `Special Court, as the case may be; and such communication shall also be sent to the purchaser if the`
  line `sample was taken under section 40.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (5792)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Recognition and accreditation of laboratories, research institutions and referral food laboratory.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5792&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Food Authority may notify food laboratories and research institutions accredited by`
  line `National Accreditation Board for Testing and Calibration Laboratories or any other accreditation agency`
  line `for the purposes of carrying out analysis of samples by the Food Analysts under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Food Authority shall, establish or recognise by notification, one or more referral food`
  line `laboratory or laboratories to carry out the functions entrusted to the referral food laboratory by this Act or`
  line `any rules and regulations made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(3) The Food Authority may frame regulations specifying--`
  line
  line `(a) the functions of food laboratory and referral food laboratory and the local area or areas within which such functions may be carried out;`
  line
  line `(b) the procedure for submission to the said laboratory of samples of articles of food for analysis`
  line `or tests, the forms of the laboratory's reports thereon and the fees payable in respect of such reports;`
  line and
  line
  line `(c) such other matters as may be necessary or expedient to enable the said laboratory to carry out`
  line `its functions effectively.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (5793)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Recognition of organisation or agency for food safety audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5793&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `The Food Authority may`
  line `recognise any organisation or agency for the purposes of food safety audit and checking compliance with`
  line `food safety management systems required under this Act or the rules and regulations made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (5794)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Food Analysts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5794&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner of Food Safety may, by notification, appoint such persons as`
  line `he thinks fit, having the qualifications prescribed by the Central Government, to be Food Analysts for`
  line `such local areas as may be assigned to them by the Commissioner of Food Safety:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person, who has any financial interest in the manufacture or sale of any article of`
  line `food shall be appointed to be a Food Analyst under this section:`
  line
  line `Provided further that different Food Analysts may be appointed for different articles of food.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (5795)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Functions of Food Analyst.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5795&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receipt of a package containing a sample for analysis from a`
  line `Food Safety Officer or any other person, the Food Analyst shall compare the seal on the container and the`
  line `outer cover with specimen impression received separately and shall note the conditions of the seal`
  line `thereon:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case a sample container received by the Food Analyst is found to be in broken`
  line `condition or unfit for analysis, he shall within a period of seven days from the date of receipt of such`
  line `sample inform the Designated Officer about the same and send requisition to him for sending second part`
  line `of the sample.`
  line
  line `(2) The Food Analyst shall cause to be analysed such samples of article of food as may be sent to him`
  line `by Food Safety Officer or by any other person authorised under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The Food Analyst shall, within a period of fourteen days from the date of receipt of any sample`
  line `for analysis, send--`
  line
  line `(i) where such sample is received under section 38 or section 47, to the Designated Officer, four`
  line `copies of the report indicating the method of sampling and analysis; and`
  line
  line `(ii) where such sample is received under section 40, a copy of the report indicating the method of`
  line `sampling and analysis to the person who had purchased such article of food with a copy to the`
  line `Designated Officer:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case the sample cannot be analysed within fourteen days of its receipt, the Food`
  line `Analyst shall inform the Designated Officer and the Commissioner of Food Safety giving reasons and`
  line `specifying the time to be taken for analysis.`
  line
  line `(4) An appeal against the report of Food Analyst shall lie before the Designated Officer who shall, if`
  line `he so decides, refer the matter to the referral food laboratory as notified by the Food Authority for`
  line opinion.
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (5796)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Sampling and analysis.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5796&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a Food Safety Officer takes a sample of food for analysis, he`
  line shall--
  line
  line `(a) give notice in writing of his intention to have it so analysed to the person from whom he has`
  line `taken the sample and to the person, if any, whose name, address and other particulars have been`
  line disclosed;
  line
  line `(b) except in special cases as may be provided by rules made under this Act, divide the sample`
  line `into four parts and mark and seal or fasten up each part in such a manner as its nature permits and`
  line `take the signature or thumb impression of the person from whom the sample has been taken in such`
  line `place and in such manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such person refuses to sign or put his thumb impression, the Food Safety`
  line `Officer shall call upon one or more witnesses and take his signature or thumb impression, in lieu of`
  line `the signature or thumb impression of such person;`
  line
  line `(c) (i) send one of the parts for analysis to the Food Analyst under intimation to the Designated`
  line Officer;
  line
  line `(ii) send two parts to the Designated Officer for keeping these in safe custody; and`
  line
  line `(iii) send the remaining part for analysis to an accredited laboratory, if so requested by the food`
  line `business operator, under intimation to the Designated Officer:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the test reports received under sub-clauses (i) and (iii) are found to be at variance,`
  line `then the Designated Officer shall send one part of the sample kept in his custody, to referral laboratory for`
  line `analysis, whose decision thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `(2) When a sample of any article of food or adulterant is taken, the Food Safety Officer shall, by the`
  line `immediate succeeding working day, send the sample to the Food Analyst for the area concerned for`
  line `analysis and report.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the part of the sample sent to the Food Analyst is lost or damaged, the Designated Officer`
  line `shall, on a requisition made to him, by the Food Analyst or the Food Safety Officer, despatch one of the`
  line `parts of the sample sent to him, to the Food Analyst for analysis.`
  line
  line `(4) An article of food or adulterant seized, unless destroyed, shall be produced before the Designated`
  line `Officer as soon as possible and in any case not later than seven days after the receipt of the report of the`
  line `Food Analyst:`
  line
  line `Provided that if an application is made to the Designated Officer in this behalf by the person from`
  line `whom any article of food has been seized, the Designated Officer shall by order in writing direct the Food`
  line `Safety Officer to produce such article before him within such time as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(5) In case of imported articles of food, the authorised officer of the Food Authority shall take its`
  line `sample and send to the Food Analyst of notified laboratory for analysis who shall send the report within a`
  line `period of five days to the authorised officer.`
  line
  line `(6) The Designated Officer, the Food Safety Officer, the authorised officer and the Food Analyst`
  line `shall follow such procedure as may be specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (5797)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `General provisions relating to offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5797&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person may render any article of food injurious`
  line `to health by means of one or more of the following operations, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) adding any article or substance to the food;`
  line
  line `(b) using any article or substance as an ingredient in the preparation of the food;`
  line
  line `(c) abstracting any constituents from the food; or`
  line
  line `(d) subjecting the food to any other process or treatment,`
  line
  line `with the knowledge that it may be sold or offered for sale or distributed for human consumption.`
  line
  line `(2) In determining whether any food is unsafe or injurious to health, regard shall be had to--`
  line
  line `(a) (i) the normal conditions of use of the food by the consumer and its handling at each stage of`
  line `production, processing and distribution;`
  line
  line `(ii) the information provided to the consumer, including information on the label, or other`
  line `information generally available to the consumer concerning the avoidance of specific adverse health`
  line `effects from a particular food or category of foods not only to the probable, immediate or short-term`
  line `or long-term effects of that food on the health of a person consuming it, but also on subsequent`
  line generations;
  line
  line `(iii) to the probable cumulative toxic effects;`
  line
  line `(iv) to the particular health sensitivities of a specific category of consumers where the food is`
  line `intended for that category of consumers; and`
  line
  line `(v) also to the probable cumulative effect of food of substantially the same composition on the`
  line `health of a person consuming it in ordinary quantities;`
  line
  line `(b) the fact where the quality or purity of the article, being primary food, has fallen below the`
  line `specified standard or its constituents are present in quantities not within the specified limits of`
  line `variability, in either case, solely due to natural causes and beyond the control of human agency, then`
  line `such article shall not be deemed to be unsafe or sub-standard or food containing extraneous matter.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "injury", includes any impairment, whether`
  line `permanent or temporary, and "Injurious to health" shall be construed accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (5798)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `General provisions relating to penalty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5798&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `While adjudging the quantum of penalty under this`
  line `Chapter, the Adjudicating Officer or the Tribunal, as the case may be, shall have due regard to the`
  line `following:--`
  line
  line `(a) the amount of gain or unfair advantage, wherever quantifiable, made as a result of the`
  line contravention,
  line
  line `(b) the Amount of loss caused or likely to cause to any person as a result of the contravention,`
  line
  line `(c) the repetitive nature of the contravention,`
  line
  line `(d) whether the contravention is without his knowledge, and`
  line
  line `(e) any other relevant factor.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (5799)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Penalty for selling food not of the nature or substance or quality demanded.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5799&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `Any person who`
  line `sells to the purchaser's prejudice any food which is not in compliance with the provisions of this Act or`
  line `the regulations made thereunder, or of the nature or substance or quality demanded by the purchaser, shall`
  line `be liable to a penalty not exceeding five lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the persons covered under sub-section (2) of section 31, shall for such non-compliance`
  line `be liable to a penalty not exceeding twenty-five thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (5800)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Penalty for sub-standard food.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5800&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `Any person who whether by himself or by any other person on`
  line `his behalf manufactures for sale or stores or sells or distributes or imports any article of food for human`
  line `consumption which is sub-standard, shall be liable to a penalty which may extend to five lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (5801)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Penalty for misbranded food.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5801&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who whether by himself or by any other person`
  line `on his behalf manufactures for sale or stores or sells or distributes or imports any article of food for`
  line `human consumption which is misbranded, shall be liable to a penalty which may extend to three lakh`
  line rupees.
  line
  line `(2) The Adjudicating Officer may issue a direction to the person found guilty of an offence under this`
  line `section, for taking corrective action to rectify the mistake or such article of food shall be destroyed.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (5802)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Penalty for misleading advertisement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5802&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `Any person who publishes, or is a party to the`
  line `publication of an advertisement, which--`
  line
  line `(a) falsely describes any food; or`
  line
  line `(b) is likely to mislead as to the nature or substance or quality of any food or gives false`
  line guarantee,
  line
  line `shall be liable to a penalty which may extend to ten lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) In any proceeding the fact that a label or advertisement relating to any article of food in respect of`
  line `which the contravention is alleged to have been committed contained an accurate statement of the`
  line `composition of the food shall not preclude the court from finding that the contravention was committed.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (5803)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Penalty for food containing extraneous matter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5803&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `Any person whether by himself or by any other`
  line `person on his behalf manufactures for sale or stores or sells or distributes or imports any article of food`
  line `for human consumption containing extraneous matter, shall be liable to a penalty which may extend to`
  line `one lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (5804)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Penalty for failure to comply with the directions of Food Safety Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5804&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `If a food business`
  line `operator or importer without reasonable ground, fails to comply with the requirements of this Act or the`
  line `rules or regulations or orders issued thereunder, as directed by the Food Safety Officer, he shall be liable`
  line `to a penalty which may extend to two lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (5805)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Penalty for unhygienic or unsanitary processing or manufacturing of food.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5805&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `Any person who,`
  line `whether by himself or by any other person on his behalf, manufactures or processes any article of food for`
  line `human consumption under unhygienic or unsanitary conditions, shall be liable to a penalty which may`
  line `extend to one lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (5806)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Penalty for possessing adulterant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5806&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this chapter, if any person`
  line `who whether by himself or by any other person on his behalf, imports or manufactures for sale, or stores,`
  line `sells or distribute any adulterant shall be liable--`
  line
  line `(i) where such adulterant is not injurious to health, to a penalty not exceeding two lakh rupees;`
  line
  line `(ii) where such adulterant is injurious to health, to a penalty not exceeding ten lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) In a proceeding under sub-section (1), it shall not be a defence that the accused was holding such`
  line `adulterant on behalf of any other person.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (5807)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Penalty for contraventions for which no specific penalty is provided.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5807&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `Whoever contravenes`
  line `any provisions of this Act or the rules or regulations made thereunder, for the contravention of which no`
  line `penalty has been separately provided in this Chapter, shall be liable to a penalty which may extend to two`
  line `lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (5808)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Punishment for unsafe food.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule, for certain words (w.e.f. 7-11-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5808&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `Any person who, whether by himself or by any other person on`
  line `his behalf, manufactures for sale or stores or sells or distributes or imports any article of food for human`
  line `consumption which is unsafe, shall be punishable,--`
  line
  line `(i) where such failure or contravention does not result in injury, with ^1[imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to three months and also with fine which may extend to three lakh rupees];`
  line
  line `(ii) where such failure or contravention results in a non-grievous injury, with imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to one year and also with fine which may extend to three lakh rupees;`
  line
  line `(iii) where such failure or contravention results in a grievous injury, with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to six years and also with fine which may extend to five lakh rupees;`
  line
  line `(iv) where such failure or contravention results in death, with imprisonment for a term which shall`
  line `not be less than seven years but which may extend to imprisonment for life and also with fine which`
  line `shall not be less than ten lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (5809)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Punishment for interfering with seized items.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5809&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `If a person without the permission of the Food`
  line `Safety Officer, retains, removes or tampers with any food, vehicle, equipment, package or labelling or`
  line `advertising material or other thing that has been seized under this Act, he shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months and also with fine which may extend to two`
  line `lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (5810)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Punishment for false information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5810&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `If a person, in connection with a requirement or direction`
  line `under this Act, provides any information or produces any document that the person knows is false or`
  line `misleading, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three months and`
  line `also with fine which may extend to two lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (5811)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Punishment for obstructing or impersonating a Food Safety Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5811&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `If a person without`
  line `reasonable excuse, resists, obstructs, or attempts to obstruct, impersonate, threaten, intimidate or assault a`
  line `Food Safety Officer in exercising his functions under this Act, he shall be punishable with imprisonment`
  line `for a term which may extend to three months and also with fine which may extend to one lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (5812)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Punishment for carrying out a business without licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5812&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `63. ^1[Penalty] for carrying out a business without`
  line licence.--
  line `If any person or food business operator`
  line `(except the persons exempted from licensing under sub-section (2) of section 31 of this Act), himself or`
  line `by any person on his behalf who is required to obtain licence, manufacturers, sells, stores or distributes or`
  line `imports any article of food without licence, shall be ^1[liable to penalty which may extend to ten lakh`
  line rupees].
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 2 and Schedule, ibid., for "Punishment" (w.e.f. 7-11-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2 and Schedule, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 7-11-2023)`
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (5813)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Punishment for subsequent offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5813&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `If any person, after having been previously convicted of`
  line `an offence punishable under this Act subsequently commits and is convicted of the same offence, he shall`
  line `be liable to--`
  line
  line `(i) twice the punishment, which might have been imposed on a first conviction, subject to the`
  line `punishment being maximum provided for the same offence;`
  line
  line `(ii) a further fine on daily basis which may extend up to one lakh rupees, where the offence is a`
  line `continuing one; and`
  line
  line `(iii) his licence shall be cancelled.`
  line
  line `(2) The Court may also cause the offender's name and place of residence, the offence and the penalty`
  line `imposed to be published at the offender's expense in such newspapers or in such other manner as the`
  line `court may direct and the expenses of such publication shall be deemed to be part of the cost attending the`
  line `conviction and shall be recoverable in the same manner as a fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (5814)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Compensation in case of injury or death of consumer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5814&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the other`
  line `provisions of this Chapter, if any person whether by himself or by any other person on his behalf,`
  line `manufactures or distributes or sells or imports any article of food causing injury to the consumer or his`
  line `death, it shall be lawful for the Adjudicating Officer or as the case may be, the court to direct him to pay`
  line `compensation to the victim or the legal representative of the victim, a sum--`
  line
  line `(a) not less than five lakh rupees in case of death;`
  line
  line `(b) not exceeding three lakh rupees in case of grievous injury; and`
  line
  line `(c) not exceeding one lakh rupees, in all other cases of injury:`
  line
  line `Provided that the compensation shall be paid at the earliest and in no case later than six months from`
  line `the date of occurrence of the incident:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in case of death, an interim relief shall be paid to the next of the kin within thirty`
  line `days of the incident.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person is held guilty of an offence leading to grievous injury or death, the`
  line `Adjudicating Officer or the court may cause the name and place of residence of the person held guilty, the`
  line `offence and the penalty imposed to be published at the offenders expense in such newspapers or in such`
  line `other manner as the Adjudicating Officer or the court may direct and the expenses of such publication`
  line `shall be deemed to be part of the cost attending the conviction and shall be recoverable in the same`
  line `manner as a fine.`
  line
  line `(3) The Adjudicating Officer or the court may also,--`
  line
  line `(a) order for cancellation of licence, re-call of food from market, forfeiture of establishment and`
  line `property in case of grievous injury or death of consumer;`
  line
  line `(b) issue prohibition orders in other cases.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (5815)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5815&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act which has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who at the time the offence was committed was in charge of, and was responsible`
  line `to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a company has different establishments or branches or different units in any`
  line `establishment or branch, the concerned Head or the person in-charge of such establishment, branch, unit`
  line `nominated by the company as responsible for food safety shall be liable for contravention in respect of`
  line `such establishment, branch or unit:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or`
  line `that he exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty`
  line `of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purpose of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means anybody corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (5816)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Penalty for contravention of provisions of this Act in case of import of articles of food to be in addition to penalties provided under any other Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5816&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `Any person who imports any article of food`
  line `which is in contravention of the provisions of this Act, rules and regulations made thereunder, shall, in`
  line `addition to any penalty to which he may be liable under the provisions of the Foreign Trade`
  line `(Development and Regulation) Act, 1992 (22 of 1992) and the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962) be also`
  line `liable under this Act and shall be proceeded against accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) Any such article of food shall be destroyed or returned to the importer, if permitted by the`
  line `competent authority under the Foreign Trade (Development and Regulation) Act, 1992 (22 of 1992) or`
  line `the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962), or any other Act, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (5817)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title Adjudication.
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5817&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of adjudication under this Chapter, an officer not below the rank`
  line `of Additional District Magistrate of the district where the alleged offence is committed, shall be notified`
  line `by the State Government as the Adjudicating Officer for adjudication in the manner as may be prescribed`
  line `by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Adjudicating Officer shall, after giving the person a reasonable opportunity for making`
  line `representation in the matter, and if, on such inquiry, he is satisfied that the person has committed the`
  line `contravention of provisions of this Act or the rules or the regulations made thereunder, impose such`
  line `penalty as he thinks fit in accordance with the provisions relating to that offence.`
  line
  line `(3) The Adjudicating Officer shall have the powers of a civil court and--`
  line
  line `(a) all proceedings before him shall be deemed to be judicial proceedings within the meaning of`
  line `sections 193 and 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860);`
  line
  line `(b) shall be deemed to be a court for the purposes of sections 345 and 346 of the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `(4) While adjudicating the quantum of penalty under this Chapter, the Adjudicating Officer shall have`
  line `due regard to the guidelines specified in section 49.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (5818)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Power to compound offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5818&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner of Food Safety may, by order, empower the`
  line `Designated Officer, to accept from petty manufacturers who himself manufacture and sell any article of`
  line `food, retailers, hawkers, itinerant vendors, temporary stall holders against whom a reasonable belief exists`
  line `that he has committed an offence or contravention against this Act, payment of a sum of money by way of`
  line `composition of the offence which such person is suspected to have committed.`
  line
  line `(2) On the payment of such sum of money to such officer, the suspected person, if in custody, shall be`
  line `discharged and no further proceedings in respect of the offence shall be taken against such person.`
  line
  line `(3) The sum of money accepted or agreed to be accepted as composition under sub section (1), shall`
  line `not be more than one lakh rupees and due regard shall be made to the guidelines specified in section 49:`
  line
  line `Provided that no offence, for which punishment of imprisonment has been prescribed under this Act,`
  line `shall be compounded.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (5819)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Establishment of Food Safety Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5819&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government or as the case may`
  line `be, the State Government may, by notification, establish one or more tribunals to be known as the Food`
  line `Safety Appellate Tribunal to hear appeals from the decisions of the Adjudicating Officer under section 68.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be, shall prescribe, the matters`
  line `and areas in relation to which the Tribunal may exercise jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(3) The Tribunal shall consist of one person only (hereinafter referred to as the Presiding Officer of`
  line `the Tribunal) to be appointed, by notification, by the Central Government or the State Government, as the`
  line `case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall be qualified for appointment as a Presiding Officer to the Tribunal`
  line `unless he is or has been a District Judge.`
  line
  line `(4) The qualifications, appointment, term of office, salary and allowances, resignation and removal of`
  line `the Presiding Officer shall be such as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) The procedure of appeal and powers of the Tribunal shall be such as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (5820)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Procedure and powers of the Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5820&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Tribunal shall not be bound by the procedure laid`
  line `down by the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) but shall be guided by the principles of natural`
  line `justice and, subject to the other provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder, the Tribunal shall`
  line `have powers to regulate its own procedure including the place at which it shall have its sittings.`
  line
  line `(2) The Tribunal shall have, for the purposes of discharging its functions under this Act, the same`
  line `powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), while trying a`
  line `suit, in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents or other electronic records;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents;`
  line
  line `(e) reviewing its decisions;`
  line
  line `(f) dismissing an application for default or deciding it ex parte;`
  line
  line `(g) any other matter which may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Every proceeding before the Tribunal shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the`
  line `meaning of sections 193 and 228, and for the purposes of section 196 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of`
  line `1860), it shall be deemed to be a civil court for all the purposes of section 195 and Chapter XXVI of the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `(4) The appellant may either appear in person or authorise one or more legal practitioners or any of its`
  line `officers to represent his case before the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(5) The provisions of the Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963), shall, except as otherwise provided in`
  line `this Act, apply to an appeal made to the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(6) Any person aggrieved by any decision or order of the Tribunal may file an appeal to the High`
  line `Court within sixty days from the date of communication of the decision or order of the Tribunal to him on`
  line `any question of fact or law arising out of such order:`
  line
  line `Provided that the High Court may, if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause`
  line `from filing the appeal within the said period, allow it to be filed within a further period not exceeding`
  line `sixty days.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (5821)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Civil court not to have jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5821&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `No civil court shall have jurisdiction to entertain any suit or`
  line `proceeding in respect of any matter which an Adjudicating Officer or the Tribunal is empowered by or`
  line `under this Act to determine and no injunction shall be granted by any court or other authority in respect of`
  line `any action taken or to be taken in pursuance of any power conferred by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (5822)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Power of court to try cases summarily.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5822&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), all offences not triable by a Special Court, shall be tried in a`
  line `summary way by a Judicial Magistrate of the first class or by a Metropolitan Magistrate and the`
  line `provisions of sections 262 to 265 (both inclusive) of the said Code shall, as far as may be, apply to such a`
  line `trial:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of any conviction in a summary trial under this section, it shall be lawful for`
  line `the Magistrate to pass a sentence of imprisonment for a term not exceeding one year:`
  line
  line `Provided further that when at the commencement of, or in the course of, a summary trial under this`
  line `section, it appears to the Magistrate that the nature of the case is such that a sentence of imprisonment for`
  line `a term exceeding one year may have to be passed or that it is, for any other reason, undesirable to try the`
  line `case summarily, the Magistrate shall after hearing the parties, record an order to that effect and thereafter`
  line `recall any witness who may have been examined and proceed to hear or rehear the case in the manner`
  line `provided by the said Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (5823)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Special courts and Public Prosecutor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5823&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or in`
  line `the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), the Central Government or the State Government in`
  line `their respective jurisdictions may, if consider expedient and necessary in the public interest, for the`
  line `purposes of the trial of offences relating to grievous injury or death of the consumer for which`
  line `punishment of imprisonment for more than three years has been prescribed under this Act, constitute, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, as many Special Courts with the concurrence of the Chief Justice of`
  line `the High Court as may be necessary for such area or areas and for exercising such jurisdiction, as may be`
  line `specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) A Special Court may, on its own motion, or on an application made by the Public Prosecutor and`
  line `if it considers it expedient or desirable so to do, sit for any of its proceedings at any place other than its`
  line `ordinary place of sitting.`
  line
  line `(3) The trial under this Act of any offence by a Special Court shall have precedence over the trial of`
  line `any other case against the accused in any other court (not being a Special Court) and shall be concluded in`
  line `preference to the trial of such other case and accordingly the trial of such other case shall remain in`
  line abeyance.
  line
  line `(4) For every Special Court, the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be,`
  line `shall appoint a person to be the Public Prosecutor and may appoint more than one person to be the`
  line `Additional Public Prosecutors:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be, may also appoint`
  line `for any case or class or group of cases, a Special Public Prosecutor.`
  line
  line `(5) A person shall not be qualified to be appointed as a Public Prosecutor or an Additional Public`
  line `Prosecutor or a Special Public Prosecutor under this section unless he has been in practice as an Advocate`
  line `for not less than seven years or has held any post, for a period of not less than seven years, under the`
  line `Union or a State, requiring special knowledge of law.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (5824)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Power to transfer cases to regular courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5824&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `Where, after taking cognizance of any offence, a`
  line `Special Court is of the opinion that the offence is not triable by it, it shall, notwithstanding that it has no`
  line `jurisdiction to try such offence, transfer the case for the trial of such offence to any court having`
  line `jurisdiction under the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) and the court to which the case is`
  line `transferred may proceed with the trial of the offence as if it had taken cognizance of the offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (5825)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5825&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by a decision or order of a Special Court may, on payment of`
  line `such fee as may be prescribed by the Central Government and after depositing the amount, if any,`
  line `imposed by way of penalty, compensation or damage under this Act, within forty-five days from the date`
  line `on which the order was served, prefer an appeal to the High Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that the High Court may entertain any appeal after the expiry of the said period of forty-five`
  line `days, if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause for filing the appeal within the`
  line `said period.`
  line
  line `(2) An appeal preferred under this section shall be disposed of by the High Court by a bench of not`
  line `less than two judges.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (5826)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Time limit for prosecutions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5826&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, no court shall take`
  line `cognizance of an offence under this Act after the expiry of the period of one year from the date of`
  line `commission of an offence:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Commissioner of Food Safety may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, approve`
  line `prosecution within an extended period of up to three years.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (5827)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Power of court to implead manufacturer, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5827&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `Where at any time during the trial of any offence`
  line `under this Act alleged to have been committed by any person, not being the importer, manufacturer,`
  line `distributor or dealer of any article of food, the court, is satisfied, on the evidence adduced before it, that`
  line `such importer, manufacturer, distributor or dealer is also concerned with that offence, then the court may,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (3) of section 319 of the Code of Criminal Procedure,`
  line `1973 (2 of 1974), or in section 71 of this Act, proceed against him as though a prosecution has been`
  line `instituted under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (5828)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Magistrate’s power to impose enhanced punishment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5828&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `section 29 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), it shall be lawful for the court of ordinary`
  line `jurisdiction to pass any sentence authorised by this Act, except a sentence of imprisonment for a term`
  line `exceeding six years in excess of his powers under the said section.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (5829)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Defences which may or may not be allowed in prosecution under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5829&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `(A) Defence`
  line `relating to publication of advertisements--`
  line
  line `(1) In any proceeding for an offence under this Act in relation to the publication of an`
  line `advertisement, it is a defence for a person to prove that the person carried on the business of`
  line `publishing or arranging for the publication of advertisements and that the person published or`
  line `arranged for the publication of the advertisement in question in the ordinary course of that`
  line business.
  line
  line `(2) Clause (1) does not apply if the person--`
  line
  line `(a) should reasonably have known that the publication of the advertisement was an`
  line `offence; or`
  line
  line `(b) had previously been informed in writing by the relevant authority that publication of`
  line `such an advertisement would constitute an offence; or`
  line
  line `(c) is the food business operator or is otherwise engaged in the conduct of a food business`
  line `for which the advertisements concerned were published.`
  line
  line `(B) Defence of due diligence--`
  line
  line `(1) In any proceedings for an offence, it is a defence if it is proved that the person took all`
  line `reasonable precautions and exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of the offence`
  line `by such person or by another person under the persons control.`
  line
  line `(2) Without limiting the ways in which a person may satisfy the requirements of clause (1), a`
  line `person satisfies those requirements if it is proved--`
  line
  line `(a) that the commission of the offence was due to--`
  line
  line `(i) an act or default of another person; or`
  line
  line `(ii) reliance on information supplied by another person; and`
  line
  line `(b) (i) the person carried out all such checks of the food concerned as were reasonable in`
  line `all the circumstances; or`
  line
  line `(ii) it was reasonable in all the circumstances to rely on checks carried out by the person`
  line `who supplied such food to the person; and`
  line
  line `(c) that the person did not import the food into the jurisdiction from another country; and`
  line
  line `(d) in the case of an offence involving the sale of food, that--`
  line
  line `(i) the person sold the food in the same condition as and when the person purchased`
  line `it; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the person sold the food in a different condition to that in which the person`
  line `purchased it, but that the difference did not result in any contravention of this Act or the`
  line `rules and regulations made thereunder; and`
  line `the alleged offence that the persons act or omission would constitute an offence under the`
  line `relevant section.`
  line
  line `(3) In sub-clause (a) of clause (2), another person does not include a person who was--`
  line
  line `(a) an employee or agent of the defendant; or`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a defendant which is a company, a director, employee or agent of that`
  line company.
  line
  line `(4) Without limiting the ways in which a person may satisfy the requirements of clause (1)`
  line `and item (i) of sub-clause (b) of clause (2), a person may satisfy those requirements by proving`
  line that--
  line
  line `(a) in the case of an offence relating to a food business for which a food safety`
  line `programme is required to be prepared in accordance with the regulations, the person complied`
  line `with a food safety programme for the food business that complies with the requirements of`
  line `the regulations, or`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, the person complied with a scheme (for example, a quality`
  line `assurance programme or an industry code of practice) that was`
  line
  line `(i) designed to manage food safety hazards and based on national or international`
  line `standards, codes or guidelines designed for that purpose, and`
  line
  line `(ii) documented in some manner.`
  line
  line `(C) Defence of mistaken and reasonable belief not available--`
  line
  line `In any proceedings for an offence under the provisions of this Act, it is no defence that the`
  line `defendant had a mistaken but reasonable belief as to the facts that constituted the offence.`
  line
  line `(D) Defence in respect of handling food--`
  line
  line `In proceedings for an offence under section 56, it is a defence if it is proved that the person`
  line `caused the food to which the offence relates to be destroyed or otherwise disposed of immediately`
  line `after the food was handled in the manner that was likely to render it unsafe.`
  line
  line `(E) Defences of significance of the nature, substance or quality of food--`
  line
  line `It shall be no defence in a prosecution for an offence pertaining to the sale of any unsafe or`
  line `misbranded article of food to allege merely that the food business operator was ignorant of the`
  line `nature, substance or quality of the food sold by him or that the purchaser having purchased any`
  line `article for analysis was not prejudiced by the sale.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (5830)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Budget of Food Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5830&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Food Authority shall prepare, in such form and at such time`
  line `in each financial year as may be prescribed by the Central Government, its budget for the next financial`
  line `year, showing the estimated receipts and expenditure of the Food Authority and forward the same to the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Food Authority with the prior approval of the Central Government, shall adopt financial`
  line `regulation which specifies in particular, the procedure for drawing up and implementing the Authoritys`
  line budget.
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (5831)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Finances of the Food Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5831&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, after due appropriation,`
  line `make to the Food Authority grants of such sums of money as the Central Government may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The Food Authority on the recommendation of the Central Advisory Committee shall specify a`
  line `graded fee from licensed food business operators, accredited laboratories or food safety auditors to be`
  line `charged by the commissioner of Food Safety.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (5832)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Accounts and audit of Food Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5832&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Food Authority shall maintain proper accounts`
  line `and relevant records and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form as may be prescribed by`
  line `the Central Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The Comptroller and Auditor-General and any person appointed by him in connection with the`
  line `audit of the accounts of the Food Authority under this Act shall have the same rights and privileges and`
  line `authority in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General generally has in`
  line `connection with the audit of Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the`
  line `production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect any of`
  line `the offices of the Food Authority.`
  line
  line `(3) The accounts of the Food Authority, as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor- General or any`
  line `other person appointed by him in this behalf, together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government by the Food Authority and the Central Government shall cause the`
  line `audit report to be laid, as soon as may be after it is received, before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (5833)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Annual report of Food Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5833&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Food Authority shall prepare once every year, in`
  line `such form and at such time as may be prescribed by the Central Government, an annual report giving a`
  line `summary of its activities during the previous year and copies of the report shall be forwarded to the`
  line `Central Government and State Governments.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of the report received under sub-section (1) shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `received, before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (5834)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Power of Central Government to issue directions to Food Authority and obtain reports and returns.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5834&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the foregoing provisions of this Act, the Food Authority shall, in`
  line `exercise of its powers and in performance of its functions under this Act, be bound by such directions on`
  line `questions of policy, other than those relating to technical and administrative matters, as the Central`
  line `Government may give in writing to it from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Food Authority shall, as far as practicable, be given an opportunity to express its`
  line `views before any direction is given under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) If any dispute arises between the Central Government and the Food Authority as to whether a`
  line `question is or is not a question of policy, the decision of the Central Government thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `(3) The Food Authority shall furnish to the Central Government such returns or other information`
  line `with respect to its activities as the Central Government may, from time to time, require.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (5835)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `Power of Central Government to give directions to State Governments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5835&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `The Central`
  line `Government may give such directions, as it may deem necessary, to a State Government for carrying out`
  line `all or any of the provisions of this Act and the State Government shall comply with such directions.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (5836)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Members, officers of Food Authority and Commissioner of Food Safety to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5836&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `The Members, officers of the Food Authority and the Commissioners of Food Safety and their`
  line `officers shall be deemed, when acting or purporting to act in pursuance of any of the provisions of this`
  line `Act, to be public servants within the meaning section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (5837)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5837&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government, the State Government, the Food Authority and other bodies`
  line `constituted under this Act or any officer of the Central Government, the State Government or any`
  line `member, officer or other employee of such Authority and bodies or any other officer acting under this Act`
  line `for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act or the rules or regulations`
  line `made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (5838)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Overriding effect of this Act over all other food related laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5838&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall`
  line `have effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being`
  line `in force or in any instrument having effect by virtue of any law other than this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (5839)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Transfer of existing employees of Central Government Agencies governing various foods related Acts or Orders to Food Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5839&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `On and from the date of establishment of the Food`
  line `Authority, every employee holding office under the Central Government Agencies administering food`
  line `laws immediately before that date shall hold his office in the Food Authority by the same tenure and upon`
  line `the same terms and conditions of service including remuneration, leave, provident fund, retirement and`
  line `other terminal benefits as he would have held such office if the Food Authority had not been established`
  line `and shall continue to do so as an employee of the Food Authority or until the expiry of the period of six`
  line `months from that date if such employee opts not to be the employee of the Food Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (5840)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5840&sectionno=91&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) salary, terms and conditions of service of Chairperson and Members other than ex officio`
  line `Members under sub-section (2) and the manner of subscribing to an oath of office and secrecy under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(b) qualifications of Food Safety Officer under sub-section (1) of section 37;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner of taking the extract of documents seized under sub-clause (8) of section 38;`
  line
  line `(d) determination of cases for referring to appropriate courts and time-frame for such`
  line `determination under sub-section (4) of section 42;`
  line
  line `(e) qualifications of Food Analysts under section 45;`
  line
  line `(f) the manner of sending sample for analysis and details of the procedure to be followed in this`
  line `regard under sub-section (1) of section 47;`
  line
  line `(g) the procedure to be followed in adjudication of cases under sub-section (1) of section 68;`
  line
  line `(h) qualifications, terms of office, resignation and removal of Presiding Officer under sub-section`
  line `(4), the procedure of appeal and powers of Tribunal under sub-section (5) of section 70;`
  line
  line `(i) any other matter relating to procedure and powers of Tribunal under clause of sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 71;`
  line
  line `(j) the fee to be paid for preferring an appeal to the High Court under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 76;`
  line
  line `(k) form and time of preparing budget under sub-section (1) of section 81;`
  line
  line `(l) form and statement of accounts under sub-section (1) of section 83;`
  line
  line `(m) the form and time for preparing annual report by Food Authority under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 84; and`
  line
  line `(n) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed or in respect of which`
  line `provision is to be made by rules by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (5841)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 92
  title `Power of Food Authority to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5841&sectionno=92&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Food Authority may, with the previous`
  line `approval of the Central Government and after previous publication, by notification, make regulations`
  line `consistent with this Act and the rules made thereunder to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) salaries and other conditions of service of officers and other employees of the Food Authority`
  line `under sub-section (3) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(b) rules of procedure for transaction of business under sub-section (5) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(c) other functions of the Central Advisory Committee under sub-section (2) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(d) procedure of Scientific Committee and Panels under sub-section (4) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(e) notifying standards and guidelines in relation to articles of food meant for human`
  line `consumption under sub-section (2) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(f) procedure to be followed by Food Authority for transaction of business at its meetings under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 17;`
  line
  line `(g)making or amending regulations in view of urgency concerning food safety or public health`
  line `under clause (d) of sub-section (2) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(h) limits of additives under section 19;`
  line
  line `(i) limits of quantities of contaminants, toxic substance and heavy metals, etc., under section 20;`
  line
  line `(j) tolerance limit of pesticides, veterinary drugs residues, etc, under section 21;`
  line
  line `(k) the manner of marking and labelling of foods under section 23;`
  line
  line `(l) form in which guarantee shall be given under sub-section (4) of section 26;`
  line
  line `(m) conditions and guidelines relating to food recall procedures under sub-section (4) of section`
  line 28;
  line
  line `(n) regulations relating to functioning of Food Safety Officer under sub-section (5) of section 29;`
  line
  line `(o) notifying the registering authority and the manner of registration; the manner of making`
  line `application for obtaining licence, the fees payable therefore and the circumstances under which such`
  line `licence may be cancelled or forfeited under section 31;`
  line
  line `(p) the respective areas of which the Designated Officer shall be in-charge for food safety`
  line `administration under sub-section (1) of section 36;`
  line
  line `(q) procedure in getting food analysed, details of fees, etc., under sub-section of section 40;`
  line
  line `(r) functions, procedure to be followed by food laboratories under sub-section (3)of section 43;`
  line
  line `(s) procedure to be followed by officials under sub-section (6) of section 47;`
  line
  line `(t) financial regulations to be adopted by the Food Authority in drawing up its budget under subsection`
  line `(2) of section 81;`
  line
  line `(u) issue guidelines or directions for participation in Codex Meetings and preparation of response`
  line `to Codex matters; and`
  line
  line `(v) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, specified by regulations or in respect of`
  line `which provision is to be made by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (5842)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 93
  title `Laying of rules and regulations before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5842&sectionno=93&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `Every rule and every regulation made`
  line `under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it`
  line `is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation or`
  line `both Houses agree that the rule or regulation should not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (5843)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 94
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5843&sectionno=94&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the powers of the Central`
  line `Government and the Food Authority to make rules and regulations respectively, the State Government`
  line `may, after previous publication and with the previous approval of the Food Authority, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, make rules to carry out the functions and duties assigned to the State Government`
  line `and the State Commissioner of Food Safety under this Act and the rules and regulations made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) other functions of the Commissioner of Food Safety under clause (f) of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 30;`
  line
  line `(b) earmarking a fund and the manner in which reward shall be paid to a person rendering`
  line `assistance in detection of offence or apprehension of offender under section 95; and`
  line
  line `(c) any other matter which is required to be, or may be prescribed or in respect of which`
  line `provision is to be made by rules by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the State Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `made, before each House of the State Legislature where it consists of two Houses or where such State`
  line `Legislature consists of one House, before that House.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (5844)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 95
  title `Reward by State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5844&sectionno=95&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may empower the Commissioner of`
  line `Food Safety to order payment of reward to be paid to a person who renders assistance in the detection of`
  line `the offence or the apprehension of the offender, from such fund and in such manner as may be prescribed`
  line `by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (5845)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 96
  title `Recovery of penalty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5845&sectionno=96&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `A penalty imposed under this Act, if it is not paid, shall be recovered as an`
  line `arrear of land revenue and the defaulters licence shall be suspended till the penalty is paid.`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (5846)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 97
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5846&sectionno=97&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central Government may appoint in`
  line `this behalf, the enactment and Orders specified in the Second Schedule shall stand repealed:`
  line
  line `Provided that such repeal shall not affect:--`
  line
  line `(i) the previous operations of the enactment and Orders under repeal or anything duly done or`
  line `suffered there under; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any right, privilege, obligation or liability acquired, accrued or incurred under any of the`
  line `enactment or Orders under repeal; or`
  line
  line `(iii) any penalty, forfeiture or punishment incurred in respect of any offences committed against`
  line `the enactment and Orders under repeal; or`
  line
  line `(iv) any investigation or remedy in respect of any such penalty, forfeiture or punishment,`
  line
  line `and any such investigation, legal proceedings or remedy may be instituted, continued or enforced and any`
  line `such penalty, forfeiture or punishment may be imposed, as if this Act had not been passed.`
  line
  line `(2) If there is any other law for the time being in force in any State, corresponding to this Act, the`
  line `same shall upon the commencement of this Act, stand repealed and in such case, the provisions of section`
  line `6 of the General Clauses Act, 1897(10 of 1897) shall apply as if such provisions of the State law had been`
  line repealed.
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding the repeal of the aforesaid enactment and Orders, the licences issued under any`
  line `such enactment or Order, which are in force on the date of commencement of this Act, shall continue to`
  line `be in force till the date of their expiry for all purposes, as if they had been issued under the provisions of`
  line `this Act or the rules or regulations made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, no court shall`
  line `take cognizance of an offence under the repealed Act or Orders after the expiry of a period of three years`
  line `from the date of the commencement of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (5847)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 98
  title `Transitory provisions for food standards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5847&sectionno=98&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding the repeal of the enactment and`
  line `Orders specified in the Second Schedule, the standards, safety requirements and other provisions of the`
  line `Act and the rules and regulations made thereunder and Orders listed in that Schedule shall continue to be`
  line `in force and operate till new standards are specified under this Act or rules and regulations made`
  line `thereunder:`
  line
  line `Provided that anything done or any action taken under the enactment and Orders under repeal shall be`
  line `deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act and shall continue in`
  line `force accordingly unless and until superseded by anything done or by any action taken under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (5848)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 99
  title `Milk and Milk Products Order, 1992 shall be deemed to be regulations made under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5848&sectionno=99&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `On and from the date of commencement of this Act, the Milk and Milk Products Order, 1992 issued`
  line `under the Essential commodities Act, 1955 (10 of 1955) shall be deemed to be the Milk and Milk`
  line `Products Regulations, 1992 issued by the Food Authority under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Food Authority may, with the previous approval of the Central Government and after`
  line `previous publication, by notification, amend the regulations specified in sub-section to carry out the`
  line `purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (5849)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 100
  title `Amendments to the Infant Milk Substitutes, Feeding Bottles and Infant Foods (Regulation of Production, Supply and Distribution) Act, 1992.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5849&sectionno=100&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `As from the notified day, the provisions of the`
  line `Infant Milk Substitutes, Feeding Bottles and Infant Foods (Regulation of Production, Supply and`
  line `Distribution) Act, 1992 (41 of 1992) (herein referred to as the principal Act) shall apply subject to the`
  line `following amendments, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) throughout the principal Act, any reference to 'the Prevention of the Food Adulteration Act,`
  line `1954" (37 of 1954) shall be substituted by reference to "the Food Safety and Standards Act, 2006";`
  line
  line `(b) in section 12 of the principal Act, the reference to "any Food Inspector appointed under`
  line `section 9 of the Prevention of the Food Adulteration Act, 1954 (37 of 1954)" shall be substituted by`
  line `reference to "any Food Safety Officer appointed under the Food Safety and Standards Act, 2006";`
  line
  line `(c) throughout the principal Act, any reference to "Food Inspector" shall be substituted by the`
  line `expression "the Food Safety Officer"; and`
  line
  line `(d) in section 21 of the principal Act, in sub-section (1), the reference to clause (a) shall be`
  line `substituted by the following, namely:`
  line
  line `"(a) the Designated Officer or the Food Safety Officer directed under sub-section (5) of section`
  line `42 of the Food Safety and Standards Act, 2006; or".`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (5850)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 101
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101&sectionId=5850&sectionno=101&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00002_200634_1517807326101
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as may appear to be necessary, for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after of the expiry of the period of three years`
  line `from the date of commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
